'''Harry Edward Kane''' (born 28 July 1993) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for {{German football updater|BaMunich}} club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[England national football team|England national team]]. Regarded as one of the best strikers of his generation, he is [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]]'s all-time top goalscorer (280), England's all-time top goalscorer (79), and the highest-scoring English player in the [[UEFA Champions League]] (54). He is also the [[Premier League]]'s second-highest [[List of footballers with 100 or more Premier League goals|all-time goalscorer]] (213) and the seventh highest goalscorer for Bayern Munich (146).<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-03-22 |title=Kane climbs into Bayern Munich's top 10 all-time scorers with 48th goal of incredible season |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/articles/kane-climbs-bayern-munichs-top-163500516.html |access-date=2026-03-23 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> He has scored over [[List of footballers with 500 or more goals|500 career goals]] for club and country.

Beginning his senior career with Tottenham Hotspur in 2009, Kane had loan spells out to clubs across the [[English football league system|English football pyramid]], including [[Leyton Orient F.C.|Leyton Orient]], [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]], [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], and [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]]. Kane's involvement at Tottenham increased after [[Mauricio Pochettino]] became head coach in 2014, being named [[PFA Young Player of the Year]] in the [[2014–15 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|2014–15 season]]. In the [[2015–16 Premier League|2015–16]] and [[2016–17 Premier League|2016–17]] seasons, Kane finished as the league's [[List of top Premier League goal scorers by season|top goalscorer]]. In the latter campaign, he helped Tottenham finish as Premier League runners-up and was named [[PFA Fans' Player of the Year]]. In the [[2018–19 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|2018–19 season]], Kane finished as Champions League runner-up and ended the [[2020–21 Premier League|2020–21]] season as the Premier League's top goalscorer (23) and top assist provider (14). In 2023, Kane became the most expensive signing in Bundesliga history as he joined Bayern Munich in a transfer worth €110&nbsp;million. In his debut season, he scored 36 league goals, winning the [[European Golden Shoe]], and in the following season, he earned his first major trophy, winning the [[2024–25 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]].

Kane has scored [[List of international goals scored by Harry Kane|79 goals]] in [[List of men's footballers with 100 or more international caps|113 appearances]] for England, making him their all-time top goalscorer. He appeared more than 30 times at [[England national youth football team|youth international level]] and made a goalscoring debut with the senior team in March 2015, at age 21. Kane featured and scored during England's successful [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying]] campaign, and represented the country at [[UEFA Euro 2016|the tournament]]. He was named [[List of England national football team captains|England captain]] just before the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], in which he finished as the competition's top goalscorer, winning the [[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Boot|Golden Boot]], leading England to fourth place, their highest finish since [[1990 FIFA World Cup|1990]]. He led England to the runner-up position at [[UEFA Euro 2020]], marking their first appearance in the [[UEFA Euro 2020 final|final]] at the tournament and their first major final since [[1966 FIFA World Cup|1966]]. At [[UEFA Euro 2024]], Kane finished as the tournament's [[UEFA European Championship awards#Top goalscorer|joint-top scorer]] as he again captained England to the [[UEFA Euro 2024 final|final]].

==Early life==
Harry Edward Kane<ref>{{Hugman|23634|access-date=31 March 2016}}</ref> was born on 28 July 1993<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/harry-kane-230567/ |title=Harry Kane |website=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |access-date=6 December 2017 |archive-date=5 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171205235717/https://www.11v11.com/players/harry-kane-230567/ |url-status=live}}</ref> at [[Whipps Cross University Hospital]] in [[Leytonstone]], London,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/spurs-tv/2019/december/the-players-surprise-kids-at-whipps-cross-hospital/ |title=Players surprise kids at Whipps Cross Hospital... where Harry Kane was born! |publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C. |date=13 December 2019 |access-date=30 May 2025}}</ref> to Kim (née Hogg) and Patrick Kane and has one older brother, Charlie.<ref name=tottenhamhotspur>{{cite web |url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/teams/men/players/harry-kane/ |title=Harry Kane |publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C. |access-date=4 December 2022 |archive-date=16 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220516013747/https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/teams/men/players/harry-kane/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=jim/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/one-day-ill-play-for-england-london-schoolboys-dream-is-about-to-come-true-10138435.html |title=One day I'll play for England: London schoolboy's dream is about to come true |first=John |last=Dunne |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |date=27 March 2015 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=29 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129165353/https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/one-day-ill-play-for-england-london-schoolboys-dream-is-about-to-come-true-10138435.html |url-status=live}}</ref> He has Irish ancestry through his father, who was born in [[Galway]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.irishpost.com/sport/5-things-never-knew-harry-kanes-surprising-irish-roots-156293 |title=5 things you never knew about Harry Kane's surprising Irish roots |last=Beresford |first=Jack |newspaper=The Irish Post |access-date=26 June 2018 |archive-date=14 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114110103/https://www.irishpost.com/sport/5-things-never-knew-harry-kanes-surprising-irish-roots-156293 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="galway">{{cite news |url=http://www.the42.ie/harry-kane-england-2001121-Mar2015/ |publisher=The 42 |title=Let's forget about Harry Kane for Ireland, he's after getting an England call-up |date=28 March 2015 |access-date=28 March 2015 |archive-date=16 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616030345/http://www.the42.ie/harry-kane-england-2001121-Mar2015/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The family lived in [[Walthamstow]] before they moved to [[Chingford]].{{sfn|Worrall|2017|pages=5–6}} Kane attended Larkswood Primary Academy until 2004,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.guardian-series.co.uk/news/13424088.New_sporting_talent_unearthed_at_Harry_Kane_s_primary_school/ |title=New sporting talent unearthed at Harry Kane's primary school |first=Natalie |last=Glanvill |newspaper=East London and West Sussex Guardian |date=16 July 2015 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=16 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116073158/https://www.guardian-series.co.uk/news/13424088.New_sporting_talent_unearthed_at_Harry_Kane_s_primary_school/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://larkswoodlime.london/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/NEWSLETTER-WB-16th-Feb-2015.pdf |title=Larkswood Primary Academy Newsletter |date=9 February 2015 |access-date=1 October 2017 |url-status=usurped |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002022012/http://larkswoodlime.london/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/NEWSLETTER-WB-16th-Feb-2015.pdf |archive-date=2 October 2017}}</ref> followed by [[Chingford Foundation School]] (also attended by [[David Beckham]]).<ref>{{cite web |title=Hall of Fame |url=https://chingfordpedept.wordpress.com/hall-of-fame |website=Chingford Foundation School PE Department |date=18 February 2015 |access-date=3 May 2017 |archive-date=20 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020181925/https://chingfordpedept.wordpress.com/hall-of-fame/ |url-status=live}}</ref> He played football from a young age, joining a local club in Walthamstow, Ridgeway Rovers, when he was six in 1999.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44625669 |title=World Cup 2018: Harry Kane – the making of England & Tottenham striker |date=2 July 2018 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=9 July 2018 |archive-date=14 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114121649/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44625669 |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane talked about footballing in the family:

{{cquote|I think the sporting genes come from my Mum's side of the family although the topic is a hot debate in the Kane household. Dad probably won't like me saying that, but I think my granddad Eric on my Mum's side was quite a good footballer, and played at a decent level.{{sfn|Worrall|2017|page=6}}}}

Kane also said: "Most of my family were Spurs fans and I grew up 15 minutes from the ground, so I was always going to be a Spurs fan".{{sfn|Worrall|2017|page=6}} This was despite being an [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] fan in his younger years.<ref>{{cite web | last1=McNicholas | first1=James | last2=Lawrence | first2=Amy | title=Harry Kane, the Arsenal years | work=The New York Times | date=14 January 2026 | url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5393588/2024/04/09/harry-kane-arsenal-years/ }}</ref> He named former Spurs striker [[Teddy Sheringham]] his childhood idol, and saw him as a "great finisher" and a role model in his ability to get in the [[penalty area|box]] and score goals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/harry-kane-teddy-sheringham-has-been-a-great-role-model-for-me-9285534.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220509/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/harry-kane-teddy-sheringham-has-been-a-great-role-model-for-me-9285534.html |archive-date=9 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Harry Kane: Teddy Sheringham has been a great role model for me |first=Simon |last=Peach |newspaper=The Independent |location=London |date=25 April 2014 |access-date=2 February 2018}}</ref> Other childhood sporting influences he cited include David Beckham and [[Jermain Defoe]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2015/05/20/kanes-childhood-heroes-consisted-of-sheringham-beckham-and-d/ |title=Tottenham striker Harry Kane's childhood heroes consisted of Sheringham, Beckham and Defoe |first=Dale |last=O'Donnell |website=HITC |date=20 May 2015 |access-date=25 November 2018 |archive-date=14 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114061639/https://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2015/05/20/kanes-childhood-heroes-consisted-of-sheringham-beckham-and-d/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane has also spoken of his admiration for the former Brazil forward [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]], adding that he loved to watch footage of him on YouTube: "He was one of the first ones I looked at and thought, 'Wow. He's a goalscorer, I want to be a goalscorer.'"<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane: I love to watch Brazilian Ronaldo on YouTube |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/12016/11397284/harry-kane-i-love-to-watch-brazilian-ronaldo-on-youtube |access-date=29 August 2018 |website=Sky Sports |archive-date=15 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115175651/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12016/11397284/harry-kane-i-love-to-watch-brazilian-ronaldo-on-youtube |url-status=live}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Tottenham Hotspur===
====2004–2010: Youth career====
Kane first played for a local club, Ridgeway Rovers, in 1999 when he was six,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2025/05/04/harry-kane-bundesliga-bayern-munich-title-goals-kompany/ |title='This should shut up all the idiots who say Harry Kane has never won anything'|first=Matt |last=Law |work=The Telegraph |date=4 May 2025 }}</ref> and joined the [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] youth academy when he was eight years old. He was released after one season for being "a bit chubby" and not "very athletic", according to [[Liam Brady]] who was then in charge of Arsenal's academy.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/02/12/liam-brady-arsenal-released-harry-kane-bit-chubby/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/02/12/liam-brady-arsenal-released-harry-kane-bit-chubby/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Liam Brady: Arsenal released Harry Kane because he was 'a bit chubby' |first=Daniel |last=Zeqiri |date=12 February 2018 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=9 July 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref> Manager [[Arsène Wenger]] stated in November 2015 that he was disappointed that Arsenal chose to release Kane.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hytner |first=David |title=Arsène Wenger: I was angry when I found out Arsenal had let Harry Kane go |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/nov/06/arsene-wenger-arsenal-tottenham-harry-kane |access-date=8 November 2015 |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=6 November 2015 |archive-date=30 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330142123/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/nov/06/arsene-wenger-arsenal-tottenham-harry-kane |url-status=live}}</ref> He also had a trial at [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] but was not initially successful,{{sfn|Worrall|2017|page=5}} and he returned to his old club Ridgeway Rovers. In 2004, at the age of eleven, he joined [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] academy for a four- to six-week trial, and was then given another chance at Tottenham after he impressed playing for Watford against Tottenham.<ref>{{cite news |title=Record-breaking Kane proves that Watford's loss was Tottenham's emphatic gain |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/tottenham-hotspur/12070870/Record-breaking-Kane-proves-that-Watfords-loss-was-Tottenhams-emphatic-gain.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/tottenham-hotspur/12070870/Record-breaking-Kane-proves-that-Watfords-loss-was-Tottenhams-emphatic-gain.html |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |first=Gerry |last=Cox |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |date=27 December 2015 |access-date=2 February 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hertfordshiremercury.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/tottenhams-harry-kane-reveals-how-1169044 |title=Tottenham's Harry Kane reveals how Watford helped catapult him to stardom |first=Tom |last=Moore |date=5 February 2018 |newspaper=Hertfordshire Mercury |access-date=9 July 2018 |archive-date=10 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710010239/https://www.hertfordshiremercury.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/tottenhams-harry-kane-reveals-how-1169044 |url-status=live}}</ref> He first played at Tottenham as a [[midfielder]] – initially in a holding position, then as an attacking midfielder.{{sfn|Worrall|2017|page=11}}

In his early days at Tottenham, Kane did not stand out as a player as he was neither big nor was he particularly quick, but those who worked with him noted his constant desire to improve various aspects of his game.<ref name="jim" /> A couple of years after joining, he had a large [[growth spurt]] that made him taller and physically stronger.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Harry Kane: Tottenham star on how to make it as a top striker |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11675/11791817/harry-kane-tottenham-star-on-how-to-make-it-as-a-top-striker|access-date=27 June 2020 |website=Sky Sports|archive-date=20 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820104546/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11675/11791817/harry-kane-tottenham-star-on-how-to-make-it-as-a-top-striker|url-status=live}}</ref> In the [[2008–09 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|2008–09 season]], he played in the under-16s side that competed in the Copa Chivas tournament in Mexico, and the Bellinzona tournament in Switzerland, scoring three goals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Unearth themselves a striking gem |date=10 September 2010 |url=http://www.footballfancast.com/football-blogs/harry-kane-tottenham-unearth-themselves-a-striking-gem |publisher=Footballfancast |access-date=21 March 2015 |archive-date=21 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150421143020/http://www.footballfancast.com/football-blogs/harry-kane-tottenham-unearth-themselves-a-striking-gem |url-status=live}}</ref> In July 2009, on his 16th birthday, he signed a scholarship contract with Tottenham.{{sfn|Worrall|2017 |page=11}}

In the [[2009–10 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|2009–10 season]], Kane played 22 times for Tottenham's under-18s, scoring 18 goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.footballfancast.com/2010/09/football-blogs/harry-kane-tottenham-unearth-themselves-a-striking-gem |title=Tottenham unearth themselves a striking gem |date=10 September 2010 |publisher=FootballFanCast.com |access-date=15 January 2011 |archive-date=3 December 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203004154/http://www.footballfancast.com/2010/09/football-blogs/harry-kane-tottenham-unearth-themselves-a-striking-gem |url-status=dead}}</ref> Kane appeared on the first-team bench twice during the 2009–10 season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tottenham: Results/matches: 2009/10 |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/teams/team.sd?team_id=2590&teamTabs=results&season_id=139 |website=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=4 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704213811/http://www.soccerbase.com/teams/team.sd?team_id=2590&teamTabs=results&season_id=139 |url-status=live}}</ref> Both matches were in home domestic cup victories: one the [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] fixture against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] on 27 October 2009,<ref>{{cite news |title=Tottenham 2–0 Everton |url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/league_cup/8323083.stm |access-date=11 January 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=27 October 2009 |archive-date=16 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230816175622/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/league_cup/8323083.stm |url-status=live}}</ref> and the other in the [[FA Cup]] fourth-round [[Replay (association football)|replay]] against [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]] on 24 February 2010.<ref>{{cite news |last=Roopanarine |first=Les |title=Tottenham 4–0 Bolton |url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/fa_cup/8528819.stm |access-date=11 January 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=24 February 2010 |archive-date=8 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211208163825/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/fa_cup/8528819.stm |url-status=live}}</ref>

====2010–2014: Loan spells across England====
Kane signed his first professional contract with Tottenham in July 2010.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kane in O's loan |url=http://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/kane-in-os-loan-070111/ |publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C. |date=7 January 2011 |access-date=31 March 2016 |archive-date=1 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701170504/http://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/kane-in-os-loan-070111/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The then U-21 coach [[Tim Sherwood]] believed that Kane could benefit from a loan spell,{{sfn|Worrall|2017|page=12}} and on 7 January 2011, Kane moved to [[Leyton Orient F.C.|Leyton Orient]] on [[Loan (association football)|loan]] until the end of the [[2010–11 Leyton Orient F.C. season|2010–11 season]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/l/leyton_orient/9349908.stm |title=Leyton Orient sign Harry Kane & Andrew Whing |date=7 January 2011 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=15 January 2011 |archive-date=20 June 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200620134144/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/l/leyton_orient/9349908.stm |url-status=live}}</ref> Manager [[Russell Slade]] was "happy" at his arrival and said, "I'm sure he will have an impact with us over the coming months".<ref name=Harry>{{cite web |title=From Leyton Orient to Tottenham's first team via Millwall: Charting the rise of Harry Kane |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11660/9734189/from-leyton-orient-to-tottenhams-first-team-via-millwall-charting-the-rise-of-harry-kane |website=Sky Sports |access-date=18 August 2015 |archive-date=20 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220171834/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11660/9734189/from-leyton-orient-to-tottenhams-first-team-via-millwall-charting-the-rise-of-harry-kane |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his first-team debut for Orient on 15 January, coming on as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Scott McGleish]] in the 73rd minute of a 1–1 draw away to [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_div_2/9359393.stm |title=Rochdale 1–1 Leyton Orient |date=15 January 2011 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> A week later, Kane scored his first first-team goal against [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]]; making his first-ever start, an "unmarked" Kane scored from a [[Dean Cox (English footballer)|Dean Cox]] [[Free kick (association football)|free kick]] in the 57th minute as Orient eventually won 4–0.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_div_2/9362036.stm |title=Leyton Orient 4–0 Sheffield Wednesday |date=22 January 2011 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=7 February 2011 |archive-date=22 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211222075156/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_2/9362036.stm |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Four-star Orient stun Owls |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/leyton-or-vs-sheff-wed/report/216323 |website=Sky Sports |access-date=18 August 2015 |archive-date=20 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220173343/https://www.skysports.com/football/leyton-or-vs-sheff-wed/report/216323 |url-status=live}}</ref> Slade said that he was "delighted" that Kane scored a goal on his first league start.<ref name=Harry/> On 12 February, he scored twice in a 4–1 win over [[Bristol Rovers F.C.|Bristol Rovers]], after coming on as a substitute for McGleish in the 70th minute.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_2/9387845.stm |title=Leyton Orient 4–1 Bristol Rovers |date=12 February 2011 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He ended the season scoring five goals in 18 matches.<ref name=Kane>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane timeline: How has the Spurs starlet gone from peripheral figure to England goalscorer? |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/harry-kane-timeline-how-spurs-5405662 |newspaper=Daily Mirror |location=London |access-date=18 August 2015 |archive-date=26 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626110853/https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/harry-kane-timeline-how-spurs-5405662 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 25 August 2011, Kane made his first appearance for Tottenham, starting in the second leg of their [[UEFA Europa League]] qualification round against [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Hearts]], with Tottenham making changes after winning the first leg 5–0. His debut was a goalless match, although he won a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty]] after being fouled by goalkeeper [[Jamie MacDonald (footballer)|Jamie MacDonald]], who then saved the penalty which Kane took himself.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lyon |first=Sam |title=Tottenham 0–0 Hearts |url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/europe/14569541.stm |access-date=11 January 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=24 August 2011 |archive-date=19 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170819151507/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/europe/14569541.stm |url-status=live}}</ref> He went on to make six appearances in the Europa League [[2011–12 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|that season]], scoring his first Tottenham goal in the 4–0 win away to [[Shamrock Rovers F.C.|Shamrock Rovers]] on 15 December 2011.<ref>{{cite news |last=Higginson |first=Marc |title=Shamrock Rovers 0–4 Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/16081794 |access-date=11 January 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=15 August 2011 |archive-date=25 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140725033535/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/16081794 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 29 December 2011, Kane and Tottenham teammate [[Ryan Mason]] agreed to join [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]] on loan from 1 January 2012 until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Millwall agree loans for Tottenham's Ryan Mason and Harry Kane |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/16358540 |access-date=11 January 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=29 December 2011 |archive-date=25 February 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130225054117/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/16358540 |url-status=live}}</ref> After making his debut against [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]], manager [[Kenny Jackett]] said that he had "very good debut" but was "unlucky not to score". He also said that Kane would "be a good addition" for the club in the second half of the season. He went on to score seven goals in the final 14 matches of the season.<ref name=Harry/> Kane scored nine goals in 27 matches which resulted in him being named Millwall's Young Player of the Year for [[2011–12 Millwall F.C. season|2011–12]].<ref name=YPOTY>{{cite web |first=Jay |last=Taylor |title=Millwall boss Jackett hands award to Spurs loanee Kane |url=http://www.newsatden.co.uk/2612-millwall-boss-jackett-hands-award-to-spurs-loanee-kane.html |website=News at Den |date=27 April 2012 |access-date=16 December 2017 |archive-date=16 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171216193619/http://www.newsatden.co.uk/2612-millwall-boss-jackett-hands-award-to-spurs-loanee-kane.html |url-status=live}}</ref> His run of goals scored towards the end of the season has been credited with helping to raise Millwall in the table away from the threat of relegation that season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/mar/09/harry-kane-loan-millwall-tottenham-fa-cup |title=How Harry Kane's loan saved Millwall from relegation and made him a man |first=David |last=Hytner |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=9 March 2017 |access-date=19 June 2018 |archive-date=19 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619203848/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/mar/09/harry-kane-loan-millwall-tottenham-fa-cup |url-status=live}}</ref>

Kane spent the 2012–13 preseason with Tottenham, scoring a [[Hat-trick (association football)|hat-trick]] in a 6–0 away win against [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]] on 10 August 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.southendunited.co.uk/news/article/100812-southend-0-tottenham-xi-6-306078.aspx |title=Southend United finished pre-season with an embarrassing 6–0 defeat to a Tottenham Hotspur XI at Roots Hall on Friday night |publisher=Southend United F.C. |date=10 August 2012 |access-date=23 October 2014 |archive-date=25 April 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425072410/http://www.southendunited.co.uk/news/article/100812-southend-0-tottenham-xi-6-306078.aspx |url-status=live}}</ref> On 18 August, he made his [[Premier League]] debut, against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/live/match/261565/report |title=Losing start for Villas-Boas |website=Sky Sports |date=18 August 2012 |access-date=24 October 2014 |archive-date=21 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150421192026/http://www1.skysports.com/football/live/match/261565/report |url-status=live}}</ref> Coming as an 86th-minute substitute for [[Sandro (footballer, born 1989)|Sandro]], Tottenham lost 2–1.<ref name=Harry/>

On 31 August 2012, Kane joined Premier League team [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] on a season-long loan,<ref>{{cite web |title=From Leyton Orient to Tottenham's first team via Millwall: Charting the rise of Harry Kane |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11660/9734189/from-leyton-orient-to-tottenhams-first-team-via-millwall-charting-the-rise-of-harry-kane |website=Sky Sports |access-date=21 March 2015 |archive-date=20 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220171834/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11660/9734189/from-leyton-orient-to-tottenhams-first-team-via-millwall-charting-the-rise-of-harry-kane |url-status=live}}</ref> making his debut as a substitute against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/19528011 |last=Smallwood |first=Jimmy |title=Norwich 0–0 West Ham |website=BBC Sport |date=15 September 2012 |access-date=24 October 2014 |archive-date=24 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924191319/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/19528011 |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane suffered an injury, breaking a [[metatarsal bone]], in the [[2012–13 Football League Cup|League Cup]] tie against [[Doncaster Rovers F.C.|Doncaster Rovers]] in only his second appearance.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/foot-fracture-for-kane-28868527.html |title=Foot fracture for Kane |newspaper=Belfast Telegraph |date=28 September 2012 |access-date=19 June 2018 |archive-date=19 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619140744/https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/foot-fracture-for-kane-28868527.html |url-status=live}}</ref> The 19-year-old underwent his rehabilitation at Tottenham but returned to action for Norwich on 29 December 2012, coming off the bench at half time as Norwich lost 3–4 to [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.eveningnews24.co.uk/sport/norwich-city/photo-gallery-defeat-to-manchester-city-sees-norwich-city-end-2012-where-they-began-1-1756832 |title=Photo gallery: Defeat to Manchester City sees Norwich City end 2012 where they began |first=David |last=Cuffley |newspaper=Norwich Evening News |date=31 December 2012 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=2 February 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180202153906/http://www.eveningnews24.co.uk/sport/norwich-city/photo-gallery-defeat-to-manchester-city-sees-norwich-city-end-2012-where-they-began-1-1756832 |url-status=live}}</ref> However, with Tottenham having been unable to add to their attacking options during the January transfer window, they opted to recall Kane on 1 February 2013, four months before he was due to return.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/tottenham-recall-striker-harry-kane-from-norwich-8477308.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220509/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/tottenham-recall-striker-harry-kane-from-norwich-8477308.html |archive-date=9 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Tottenham recall striker Harry Kane from Norwich |newspaper=The Independent |location=London |date=1 February 2013 |access-date=24 October 2014}}</ref>

Twenty days after he was recalled to Tottenham, Kane joined [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] for the remainder of the season to aid in the club's push for automatic promotion from the Championship.<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane: Leicester City sign Tottenham striker |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/21533301 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 May 2013 |date=21 February 2013 |archive-date=24 February 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130224051702/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/21533301 |url-status=live}}</ref> He marked his home debut with a goal against [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]], in a 3–0 win on 26 February 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2013/feb/26/leicester-city-blackburn-rovers-championship |title=Resurgent Leicester City punish lacklustre Blackburn Rovers |first=Richard |last=Rae |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=26 February 2013 |access-date=19 June 2018 |archive-date=19 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619140235/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2013/feb/26/leicester-city-blackburn-rovers-championship |url-status=live}}</ref> He made 13 appearances for the [[East Midlands]] club, eight from the bench, and they reached [[2013 Football League Championship play-offs|the play-off semi-final]] before being eliminated by Watford.<ref>{{cite news |last=Sanghera |first=Mandeep |title=Watford 3–1 Leicester (agg 3–2) |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/22417772 |access-date=21 March 2015 |archive-date=24 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924192533/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/22417772 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Kane scored his first Tottenham goal of the 2013–14 season at [[White Hart Lane]] in a [[2013–14 Football League Cup|League Cup]] tie against [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]], scoring the equaliser in extra time, the match finished 2–2.<ref name="Hull City League Cup">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/24633791 |title=Tottenham 2–2 Hull (8–7 on pens) |website=BBC Sport |date=30 October 2013 |access-date=23 October 2014 |archive-date=21 December 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221093510/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/24633791 |url-status=live}}</ref> Tottenham won 8–7 on [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalties]], with Kane taking and converting the fifth of the nine sets of spot-kicks.<ref name="Hull City League Cup"/>

On 7 April 2014, Kane was given his first Premier League start for Tottenham by manager [[Tim Sherwood]], in a 5–1 win against [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]], and scored his first Premier League goal in the 59th minute.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/26814762 |last=Chowdhury |first=Saj |title=Tottenham 5–1 Sunderland |date=7 April 2014 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=24 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924203202/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/26814762 |url-status=live}}</ref> He also scored in the following match, helping Tottenham to recover from a 3–0 deficit against [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] before eventually drawing 3–3.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/26898645 |last=Cryer |first=Andy |title=West Bromwich Albion 3–3 Tottenham Hotspur |website=BBC Sport |date=12 April 2014 |access-date=19 April 2014 |archive-date=3 March 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150303214408/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/26898645 |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored for the third match in a row on 19 April, this time helping Tottenham to a 3–1 [[London derbies|London derby]] win at home over [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/26998951 |last=Sanghera |first=Mandeep |title=Tottenham Hotspur 3–1 Fulham |website=BBC Sport |date=19 April 2014 |access-date=19 April 2014 |archive-date=5 November 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151105232053/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/26998951 |url-status=live}}</ref>

====2014–2015: PFA Young Player of the Year====
[[File:Spurs 5 Chelsea 3 (16175596592).jpg|thumb|Kane (left) playing for [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] in 2015]]

Kane made his first appearance of the [[2014–15 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|2014–15 season]] as a substitute in a London [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.–West Ham United F.C. rivalry|derby]] against West Ham on the opening day of the [[2014–15 Premier League|Premier League season]], providing an [[Assist (association football)|assist]] for the match-winning goal by [[Eric Dier]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Rose |first=Gary |title=West Ham 0–1 Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/28718387 |access-date=16 August 2014 |website=BBC Sport |date=16 August 2014 |archive-date=26 January 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126175407/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/28718387 |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored in both matches against Cypriot opposition [[AEL Limassol]] in Tottenham's [[2014–15 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round#Play-off round|UEFA Europa League play-offs]], scoring an 80th-minute winner in the first leg, and opening the scoring in the 3–0 second leg victory after missing a penalty.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28945073 |last=Jurejko |first=Jonathan |title=Tottenham 3–0 AEL Limassol (agg 5–1) |website=BBC Sport |access-date=23 October 2014 |date=28 August 2014 |archive-date=24 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924211726/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28945073 |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored a late goal against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] in the [[2014–15 Football League Cup|League Cup]] to secure a 3–1 victory for Tottenham on 24 September 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29233056 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 3–1 Nottingham Forest |website=BBC Sport |date=24 September 2014 |access-date=23 October 2014 |archive-date=5 January 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160105131517/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29233056 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 23 October 2014, Kane scored his first professional hat-trick for Tottenham in a 5–1 win over [[Asteras Tripolis F.C.|Asteras Tripolis]] in the [[2014–15 UEFA Europa League group stage|group stage]] of the [[2014–15 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]].<ref name="Asteras Tripoli">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29730663 |last=Canavan |first=Steve |title=Tottenham Hotspur 5–1 Asteras Tripolis |website=BBC Sport |date=23 October 2014 |access-date=23 October 2014 |archive-date=2 October 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151002065053/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29730663 |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane was forced to play [[Goalkeeper (association football)|in goal]] for the final three minutes, after [[Hugo Lloris]] had been sent off with no substitutions remaining, and conceded a goal when he dropped a free-kick from [[Jerónimo Barrales]].<ref name="Asteras Tripoli"/>

On 2 November 2014, Kane came on as a second-half substitute in Tottenham's 2–1 win over [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] and scored his first Premier League goal of the season to win the match in the 90th minute.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/29775975 |title=Aston Villa 1–2 Tottenham Hotspur |first=Mike |last=Whalley |website=BBC Sport |access-date=8 December 2019 |archive-date=25 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210425104209/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/29775975 |url-status=live}}</ref> Manager [[Mauricio Pochettino]], who was appointed to replace Sherwood and had a rocky start at the club, has since said that this goal saved him from the sack.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/premier-league/2017-2018/mauricio-pochettino-harry-kane-saved-me-from-sack-at-tottenham_sto6335534/story.shtml |title=Mauricio Pochettino: Harry Kane Saved Me From Sack at Tottenham |date=16 September 2017 |publisher=Eurosport |access-date=6 February 2023|archive-date=19 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170919195944/http://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/premier-league/2017-2018/mauricio-pochettino-harry-kane-saved-me-from-sack-at-tottenham_sto6335534/story.shtml|url-status=live}}</ref> Henceforth, under Pochettino, Kane became a regular in Spurs' starting line-up. He was selected to start a week later for the first time in this Premier League season, and although the team lost 2–1 at home to [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/29868773 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 1–2 Stoke City |date=9 November 2014 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=16 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416145909/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/29868773 |url-status=live}}</ref> he retained his place in the first XI for Spurs' 2–1 win away to Hull City on 23 November, scoring the team's equalising goal.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30072815 |title=Hull City 1–2 Tottenham Hotspur |first=Andy |last=Cryer |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=22 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150222130208/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30072815 |url-status=live}}</ref> Between 14 and 26 December, Kane scored in three consecutive 2–1 wins for Tottenham, against [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/30366054 |title=Swansea City 1–2 Tottenham Hotspur |date=14 December 2014 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=27 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227050426/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/30366054 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/30459791 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 2–1 Burnley |date=20 December 2014 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=15 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215013004/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/30459791 |url-status=live}}</ref> and Leicester City.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/30544152 |title=Leicester City 1–2 Tottenham Hotspur |date=26 December 2014 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=2 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210302001117/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/30544152 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 1 January 2015, Kane scored twice and won a penalty as Tottenham defeated [[Chelsea F.C.–Tottenham Hotspur F.C. rivalry|rivals]] and league leaders [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] 5–3,<ref>{{cite news |last=Shemilt |first=Stephan |title=Tottenham 5–3 Chelsea |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30600753 |access-date=2 January 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=1 January 2015 |archive-date=3 December 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151203185809/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30600753 |url-status=live}}</ref> and he scored a further two in a 3–0 away win against West Bromwich Albion on 31 January, including one from a penalty.<ref>{{cite news |last=Oscroft |first=Tim |title=West Brom 0–3 Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30963472 |access-date=31 January 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=31 January 2015 |archive-date=13 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413045939/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30963472 |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane set up [[Christian Eriksen]]'s late equaliser against [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] on 28 January 2015, a goal which put Tottenham into the [[2015 Football League Cup final|2015 League Cup final]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Rostance |first=Tom |title=Sheff Utd 2–2 Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30910040 |access-date=2 February 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=28 January 2015 |archive-date=7 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150407100729/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30910040 |url-status=live}}</ref> His performances led to him being named as the [[Premier League Player of the Month]] for January 2015.<ref name="PremProfile"/>

On 2 February 2015, Kane signed a new five-and-a-half-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web |title=Harry Kane signs new five-year deal with Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/31090218 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=2 February 2015 |date=2 February 2015 |archive-date=22 December 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222041511/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/31090218 |url-status=live}}</ref> Five days later, he scored both of Tottenham's goals as they came from behind to defeat Arsenal in the [[North London derby]], his 21st and 22nd goals of the season across all competitions.<ref>{{cite news |last=Dawkes |first=Phil |title=Tottenham 2–1 Arsenal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31071175 |access-date=7 February 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=7 February 2015 |archive-date=6 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150406145909/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31071175 |url-status=live}}</ref> After scoring against Arsenal, [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and West Ham United, Kane was again named as the Premier League Player of the Month for February 2015,<ref name="PremProfile"/> becoming only the fourth player to win the award in consecutive months.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tottenham: Harry Kane wins second Player of the Month award |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31870169 |access-date=13 March 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=13 February 2015 |archive-date=1 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150401062123/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31870169 |url-status=live}}</ref> Tottenham lost the League Cup final 2–0 to rivals Chelsea on 1 March 2015,<ref name=2015LC>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Chelsea 2–0 Tottenham Hotspur |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31572594 |website=BBC Sport |date=1 March 2015 |access-date=16 December 2017 |archive-date=16 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616231951/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31572594 |url-status=live}}</ref> which Kane described as the "worst feeling in the world".<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane: Tottenham's League Cup defeat to Chelsea was the worst feeling in the world |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/harry-kane-tottenhams-league-cup-defeat-to-chelsea-was-the-worst-feeling-in-the-world-10079903.html |access-date=27 August 2015 |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |date=2 March 2015 |archive-date=30 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130145155/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/harry-kane-tottenhams-league-cup-defeat-to-chelsea-was-the-worst-feeling-in-the-world-10079903.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Twenty days later, he scored his first [[List of Premier League hat-tricks|Premier League hat-trick]] in a 4–3 home win over his former loan club Leicester;<ref>{{cite news |title=Tottenham 4–3 Leicester |last=Sanghera |first=Mandeep |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31883462 |access-date=21 March 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=21 March 2015 |archive-date=26 January 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126134512/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31883462 |url-status=live}}</ref> this brought him to 19 league goals in the season, making him the division's top scorer.<ref>{{cite news |last=Oliver |first=Tom |title=Harry Kane becomes the Premier League's top scorer with hat-trick for Tottenham against Leicester City |url=http://metro.co.uk/2015/03/21/harry-kane-becomes-the-premier-leagues-top-scorer-with-hat-trick-for-tottenham-against-leicester-city-5114837/ |access-date=21 March 2015 |newspaper=Metro |location=London |date=21 March 2015 |archive-date=4 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210204073343/https://metro.co.uk/2015/03/21/harry-kane-becomes-the-premier-leagues-top-scorer-with-hat-trick-for-tottenham-against-leicester-city-5114837/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 5 April, Kane [[Captain (association football)|captained]] Tottenham for the first time in a 0–0 draw with Burnley at [[Turf Moor]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/apr/05/burnley-tottenham-hotspur-premier-league-match-report |title=Battling Burnley blunt Tottenham's edge to deny captain Harry Kane |date=6 April 2015 |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |access-date=11 December 2016 |archive-date=6 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706191454/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/apr/05/burnley-tottenham-hotspur-premier-league-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref> Two weeks later, he scored his 30th goal of the season in a 3–1 win against Newcastle United at [[St James' Park]], making him the first Tottenham player to reach that milestone since [[Gary Lineker]] in [[1991–92 Football League|1991–92]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/competitions/premier-league/11548208/Newcastle-1-Tottenham-3-match-report-Harry-Kane-takes-goal-tally-to-30-for-the-season.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/competitions/premier-league/11548208/Newcastle-1-Tottenham-3-match-report-Harry-Kane-takes-goal-tally-to-30-for-the-season.html |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Newcastle 1 Tottenham 3, match report: Harry Kane takes goal tally to 30 for the season |date=19 April 2015 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London}}{{cbignore}}</ref> Later that month, he was included as one of two forwards in the [[PFA Team of the Year]], alongside Chelsea's [[Diego Costa]].<ref name=PFA1415>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32472834 |title=Chelsea's Eden Hazard named PFA Player of the Year |website=BBC Sport |date=26 April 2015 |access-date=16 December 2017 |archive-date=28 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200728002107/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32472834 |url-status=live}}</ref> He was also voted the [[PFA Young Player of the Year]].<ref name=young>{{cite web |title=Tottenham striker Harry Kane named PFA Young Player of the Year |url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/9/england/2015/04/26/11172202/tottenham-striker-harry-kane-named-pfa-young-player-of-the?ICID=HP_BN_2 |website=Goal |date=26 April 2015 |access-date=26 April 2015 |archive-date=16 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181216210845/https://www.goal.com/en/news/9/england/2015/04/26/11172202/tottenham-striker-harry-kane-named-pfa-young-player-of-the?ICID=HP_BN_2 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 24 May 2015, he headed in an Eric Dier cross for the only goal of an away win over Everton on the final day of the season to confirm fifth place for Tottenham, thus qualifying them to the group stage of the following season's UEFA Europa League. It was his 21st goal of the league campaign, equalling a Premier League club record alongside Teddy Sheringham, [[Jürgen Klinsmann]] and [[Gareth Bale]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Magowan |first=Alistair |title=Everton 0–1 Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32770847 |access-date=24 May 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=24 May 2015 |archive-date=24 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150824233533/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32770847 |url-status=live}}</ref> At the end of the season, Kane remarked that he had done more in the single campaign than he had expected to do in his whole career.<ref name=stuff/>

====2015–2016: Premier League top goalscorer====
[[File:Harry Kane (24685589756).jpg|thumb|Kane playing for [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] in 2016]]

On Tottenham's pre-season tour of Australia, Kane attracted numerous fans while visiting the [[Westfield Sydney]] shopping centre, resulting in the club sending a minibus to escort him away.<ref name=stuff>{{cite news |last=Hytner |first=David |title=Harry Kane: I achieved so much ... stuff I wanted to do in a career, I did in a season |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/aug/07/harry-kane-tottenham-interview |access-date=27 August 2015 |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=7 August 2015 |archive-date=2 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210302034008/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/aug/07/harry-kane-tottenham-interview |url-status=live}}</ref> On 29 July 2015, Tottenham were the guests in the [[2015 MLS All-Star Game]] at [[Dick's Sporting Goods Park]] in [[Commerce City, Colorado]]. They lost 2–1 to the MLS All-Stars, with Kane scoring their consolation goal in the 37th minute after beating a challenge from [[Omar Gonzalez]], and he was later substituted in the 77th minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://matchcenter.mlssoccer.com/matchcenter/2015-07-29-mls-all-star-team-vs-tottenham-hotspur/recap |title=MLS All-Stars 2, Tottenham Hotspur 1: 2015 AT&T MLS All-Star Game |first=Simon |last=Borg |publisher=Major League Soccer |date=30 July 2015 |access-date=19 June 2018 |archive-date=26 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191226170741/https://matchcenter.mlssoccer.com/matchcenter/2015-07-29-mls-all-star-team-vs-tottenham-hotspur/recap |url-status=dead}}</ref>

Kane's squad number was changed from 18 to 10, previously worn by [[Emmanuel Adebayor]]. In an interview with ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'', he said that he changed the number "to become a club legend".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/tottenham-hotspur/11803956/Harry-Kane-I-want-to-become-a-Tottenham-legend-and-change-the-image-of-players-representing-England.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/tottenham-hotspur/11803956/Harry-Kane-I-want-to-become-a-Tottenham-legend-and-change-the-image-of-players-representing-England.html |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Harry Kane: 'I want to become a Tottenham legend and change the image of players representing England' |last=Burt |first=Jason |date=14 August 2015 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |access-date=25 August 2015}}{{cbignore}}</ref> With Adebayor and [[Roberto Soldado]] having been put up for sale, he began the season as the club's only forward, and the third-choice captain behind [[Hugo Lloris]] and [[Jan Vertonghen]].<ref name=stuff/> After a 748-minute drought, he scored his first goal of the season on 26 September 2015 as Tottenham came from behind to defeat leaders Manchester City 4–1.<ref>{{cite news |last=Sanghera |first=Mandeep |title=Tottenham 4–1 Man City |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34299624 |access-date=26 September 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 September 2015 |archive-date=30 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930011252/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34299624 |url-status=live}}</ref> Eight days later, he scored an [[Own goal (association football)|own goal]] from [[Jonjo Shelvey]]'s corner kick away to Swansea City, but Tottenham fought back to a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{cite news |last=Dawkes |first=Phil |title=Swansea 2–2 Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34372499 |access-date=4 October 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=4 October 2015 |archive-date=20 October 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151020034531/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34372499 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 25 October 2015, Kane scored a hat-trick, including a penalty which he won himself, as Tottenham came from conceding a first-minute goal to triumph 5–1 away to [[AFC Bournemouth]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Bournemouth 1–5 Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34564964 |access-date=25 October 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=25 October 2015 |archive-date=26 January 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126134512/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34564964 |url-status=live}}</ref> Eight days later, he recorded his fifth goal of the season with the final goal in a 3–1 win at home to Aston Villa.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tottenham 3–1 Aston Villa |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34634659 |access-date=2 November 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=2 November 2015 |archive-date=20 November 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151120165910/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34634659 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 8 November 2015, he gave Tottenham a half-time lead against Arsenal at the [[Emirates Stadium]], albeit in a 1–1 draw;<ref>{{cite news |last=Higginson |first=Marc |title=Arsenal 1–1 Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34691295 |access-date=8 November 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=8 November 2015 |archive-date=27 November 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151127224107/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34691295 |url-status=live}}</ref> this goal past [[Petr Čech]] was from his first touch of [[Danny Rose (footballer, born 1990)|Danny Rose]]'s long pass.<ref>{{cite news |last=Pierce |first=Liam Daniel |title=Harry Kane scored gorgeous one-touch goal off of an even more beautiful long ball |url=https://sports.vice.com/en_us/article/yp8x4j/harry-kane-scores-gorgeous-one-touch-goal-off-of-an-even-more-beautiful-long-ball |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915070428/https://sports.vice.com/en_us/article/yp8x4j/harry-kane-scores-gorgeous-one-touch-goal-off-of-an-even-more-beautiful-long-ball |url-status=live |archive-date=15 September 2017 |access-date=8 November 2015 |publisher=Vice News |date=8 November 2015}}</ref>

Eighteen days after that, he recorded his ninth goal in six matches, the only one of an away match against [[Qarabağ FK|Qarabağ]], qualifying Tottenham to the [[2015–16 UEFA Europa League knockout phase|knockout stages]] of [[2015–16 UEFA Europa League|the season's UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Chowdhury |first=Saj |title=FK Qarabag 0–1 Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34896664 |access-date=26 November 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=26 November 2015 |archive-date=11 December 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151211055255/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34896664 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 December 2015, Kane made his 100th appearance for the club in a 2–0 win away to [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]], and scored his 10th goal in his last 10 matches.<ref>{{cite news |last=Dawkes |first=Phil |title=Southampton 0–2 Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/35078557 |access-date=19 December 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=19 December 2015 |archive-date=28 December 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151228173439/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/35078557 |url-status=live}}</ref> A week later, he added two more in a 3–0 win over former loan employers Norwich, putting him on 27 Premier League goals for the year 2015, breaking Sheringham's club record.<ref>{{cite news |last=Oscroft |first=Tim |title=Tottenham 3–0 Norwich |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/35139938 |access-date=26 December 2015 |date=26 December 2015 |archive-date=30 December 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151230034501/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/35139938 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 10 January 2016, he scored his 50th goal for Tottenham in a 2–2 draw against Leicester in the third round of the [[2015–16 FA Cup|FA Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Tottenham 2–2 Leicester |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/35216362 |access-date=11 January 2016 |website=BBC Sport |date=10 January 2016 |archive-date=27 January 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160127221318/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/35216362 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Kane was Premier League Player of the Month for the third time in March 2016, after scoring five goals in four games, including an angled strike from the corner of the 18-yard box in the North London derby which Kane called "one of my best goals technically".<ref name="PremProfile"/><ref>{{cite news |title=Kane: Screamer against Arsenal the best of my 150 PL goals |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/2111864 |access-date=25 October 2021 |publisher=Premier League |archive-date=26 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211026090946/https://www.premierleague.com/news/2111864 |url-status=live}}</ref> After scoring his 22nd league goal of the season in a 1–1 draw against Liverpool at [[Anfield]] on 2 April, Kane became the club's highest goalscorer in a single Premier League season, with six games of the season remaining.<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane joins elite group of Premier League goalscorers |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11675/10228695/harry-kane-joins-elite-group-of-premier-league-goalscorers |access-date=4 April 2016 |website=Sky Sports |date=4 April 2016 |archive-date=28 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128070109/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11675/10228695/harry-kane-joins-elite-group-of-premier-league-goalscorers |url-status=live}}</ref>

Kane ended the season winning the [[Premier League Golden Boot]], finishing one goal ahead of [[Sergio Agüero]] and [[Jamie Vardy]] with 25 goals.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/12028/10283818/tottenhams-harry-kane-clinches-premier-league-golden-boot |title=Tottenham's Harry Kane clinches Premier League Golden Boot |date=15 May 2016 |website=Sky Sports |access-date=16 May 2016 |archive-date=6 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210506100343/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12028/10283818/tottenhams-harry-kane-clinches-premier-league-golden-boot |url-status=live}}</ref> He was named in the PFA Team of the Year for the second consecutive season,<ref name=PFA1516>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36106596 |title=PFA awards: Leicester and Spurs dominate Premier League team |website=BBC Sport |date=21 April 2016 |access-date=6 December 2017 |archive-date=29 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629035855/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36106596 |url-status=live}}</ref> as he helped Tottenham to a third-place finish, and [[2016–17 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] qualification.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/05/16/spurs-striker-harry-kane-positive-with-progress-despite-end-of-s/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/05/16/spurs-striker-harry-kane-positive-with-progress-despite-end-of-s/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Spurs striker Harry Kane positive with progress despite end of season collapse |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |first=Luke |last=Edwards |date=19 May 2016 |access-date=16 May 2016}}{{cbignore}}</ref>

====2016–2017: League runner-up and second Golden Boot====
[[File:Manchester United v Tottenham Hotspur, December 2016 (08).JPG|thumb|Kane (centre) with his [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] teammates in 2016]]

In the absence of Hugo Lloris, Kane captained Tottenham in their opening home match of the [[2016–17 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|2016–17 season]], assisting [[Victor Wanyama]]'s winning goal as Spurs beat [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] 1–0 in a London derby at White Hart Lane.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/08/21/harry-kane-shows-promising-signs-in-a-new-role-as-tottenham-edge/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/08/21/harry-kane-shows-promising-signs-in-a-new-role-as-tottenham-edge/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Harry Kane shows promising signs in a new role as Tottenham edge past Crystal Palace |date=21 August 2016 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London}}{{cbignore}}</ref> He opened his scoring account in the fourth matchday of the [[2016–17 Premier League|Premier League season]], providing the final goal in a 4–0 win away to Stoke City.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37263919 |title=Stoke City 0–4 Tottenham Hotspur |date=10 September 2016 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=25 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210625192028/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37263919 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 14 September 2016, Kane made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut in Spurs' 2–1 loss to [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] at [[Wembley Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Flanagan |first=Chris |title=Why Harry Kane's Dortmund brace could be a genuine watershed moment |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/why-harry-kanes-dortmund-brace-could-be-a-genuine-watershed-moment |magazine=FourFourTwo |date=14 September 2017 |access-date=6 October 2017 |archive-date=31 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201231043544/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/why-harry-kanes-dortmund-brace-could-be-a-genuine-watershed-moment |url-status=live}}</ref> Four days later, he scored the winning goal against Sunderland in the Premier League, but had to be helped off the field after twisting his right ankle attempting a tackle of [[Papy Djilobodji]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37416108 |title=Harry Kane: Tottenham give no time frame over striker's ankle injury |website=BBC Sport |date=20 September 2016 |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=21 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180621122911/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37416108 |url-status=live}}</ref> Reports indicated that the ligaments in Kane's ankle were damaged, ruling him out for six-to-eight weeks.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.us/tottenham-hotspur/story/2954625/tottenham-striker-harry-kane-faces-two-months-out-with-ankle-injury-reports |title=Tottenham's Harry Kane faces two months out with ankle injury – reports |website=ESPN FC |date=19 September 2016 |access-date=20 September 2016 |archive-date=21 September 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921203413/http://www.espnfc.us/tottenham-hotspur/story/2954625/tottenham-striker-harry-kane-faces-two-months-out-with-ankle-injury-reports |url-status=live}}</ref> After missing five league matches and three in the [[2016–17 UEFA Champions League#Group E|Champions League group phase]], Kane made his return at rivals Arsenal on 6 November, scoring from the penalty spot to equalise in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2016/nov/06/arsenal-tottenham-hotspur-premier-league-match-report |title=Harry Kane spot-on to claim draw for Tottenham at Arsenal on return |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |first=Daniel |last=Taylor |date=6 November 2016 |access-date=7 November 2016 |archive-date=9 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210209042606/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2016/nov/06/arsenal-tottenham-hotspur-premier-league-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 November, he scored his first Champions League goal in the return fixture against Monaco at the [[Stade Louis II]], a game which saw Spurs eliminated from the competition with a 2–1 loss.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/11/22/monaco-vs-spurs-champions-league-live/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/11/22/monaco-vs-spurs-champions-league-live/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Monaco 2 Tottenham 1: Spurs out of Champions League as superb Hugo Lloris let down badly by team-mates |date=22 November 2016 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London}}{{cbignore}}</ref>

On 1 December 2016, Kane signed a new contract with Tottenham, keeping him at the club until 2022.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/new-deal-for-kane-011216/ |title=New deal for Kane |date=1 December 2016 |access-date=1 December 2016 |publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C. |archive-date=1 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701195259/http://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/new-deal-for-kane-011216/ |url-status=live}}</ref> On 1 January 2017, he made his 100th Premier League appearance,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2017/01/01/harry-kane-equals-thierry-henrys-goal-record-100-premier-league/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2017/01/01/harry-kane-equals-thierry-henrys-goal-record-100-premier-league/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Harry Kane equals Thierry Henry's goal record after 100 Premier League games |date=1 January 2017 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London}}{{cbignore}}</ref> scoring the first Premier League goal of the new year against Watford in the 27th minute, which he extended to a brace after scoring again six minutes later.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hertfordshiremercury.co.uk/story-30023260-detail/story.html |title=Who scored the first Premier League goal of 2017? The answer is Harry Kane! |date=1 January 2017 |newspaper=Hertfordshire Mercury |location=Hertford |access-date=15 January 2017 |archive-date=20 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230120145526/https://www.hertfordshiremercury.co.uk/story-30023260-detail/story.html |url-status=dead}}</ref> In his first match after the birth of his daughter, Kane scored a hat-trick in a 4–0 win against West Brom on 14 January.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38539373"Tottenham Hotspur 4–0 West Brom"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200708151342/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38539373 |date=8 July 2020 }}. BBC Sport. 14 January 2017. Retrieved 14 January 2017.</ref> In the fifth round of the [[2016–17 FA Cup]] on 19 February 2017, Kane scored all three goals as Tottenham beat Fulham 3–0. This meant his fifth career hat-trick, and his second in 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/38947531 |title=Fulham 0–3 Tottenham Hotspur |date=19 February 2017 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=1 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210301045450/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/38947531 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 26 February 2017, Kane once again scored a hat-trick as Tottenham beat Stoke 4–0, his third hat-trick in nine games, and his second in consecutive domestic games.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39018820 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 4–0 Stoke City |date=26 February 2017 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=30 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210330105200/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39018820 |url-status=live}}</ref> The first of these goals was his 100th in club football.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thestandard.com.hk/section-news.php?id=180149 |title=King Kane marches on – Tottenham boss in 100-goal salute to Harry the great |date=28 February 2017 |newspaper=The Standard |location=Hong Kong |access-date=6 March 2017 |archive-date=6 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170306214725/http://www.thestandard.com.hk/section-news.php?id=180149 |url-status=live}}</ref> He was named Player of the Month for the fourth time in his career in February 2017.<ref name="PremProfile"/>

In March 2017, he injured his ankle in an FA Cup match against former loan club Millwall.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/harry-kane-leaves-white-hart-10012185 |title=Harry Kane leaves White Hart Lane on crutches and in protective boot as Pochettino sweats over striker's injury |first=James |last=Whaling |newspaper=Daily Mirror |location=London |date=13 March 2017 |access-date=19 June 2018 |archive-date=1 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801154315/https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/harry-kane-leaves-white-hart-10012185 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 15 April, Kane scored his 20th Premier League goal of the season against Bournemouth on his first start in a month after returning from injury. This made him the fourth player in Premier League history to achieve 20 goals in three consecutive seasons, after [[Alan Shearer]], [[Thierry Henry]] and [[Ruud van Nistelrooy]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/04/15/harry-kane-becomes-just-the-fourth-player-to-score-20-goals-in-three-consecutive-seasons-after-bournemouth-strike-6576784/ |title=Harry Kane becomes just the fourth player in Premier League history to score 20+ goals in three consecutive seasons |last=Kearns |first=Sean |newspaper=Metro |location=London |date=15 April 2017 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=1 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201100704/https://metro.co.uk/2017/04/15/harry-kane-becomes-just-the-fourth-player-to-score-20-goals-in-three-consecutive-seasons-after-bournemouth-strike-6576784/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 20 April, Kane was named in the PFA Team of the Year for the third consecutive season.<ref name=PFA1617>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39648483 |title=PFA teams of the year: Chelsea and Tottenham dominate Premier League XI |website=BBC Sport |date=20 April 2017 |access-date=16 December 2017 |archive-date=12 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112073506/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39648483 |url-status=live}}</ref> He was also included in the six player shortlists for the [[PFA Players' Player of the Year]] and PFA Young Player of the Year awards.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thepfa.com/news/2017/4/13/pfa-mens-players-player-of-the-year |title=Men's PFA Players' Player of the Year 2017 |publisher=Professional Footballers' Association |date=13 April 2017 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=8 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210608114031/https://www.thepfa.com/news/2017/4/13/pfa-mens-players-player-of-the-year |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thepfa.com/news/2017/4/13/pfa-mens-young-player-of-the-year |title=Men's PFA Young Player of the Year 2017 |publisher=Professional Footballers' Association |date=13 April 2017 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=23 April 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170423154800/https://www.thepfa.com/news/2017/4/13/pfa-mens-young-player-of-the-year |url-status=live}}</ref> Two days later, he scored in Tottenham's 4–2 [[FA Cup semi-finals|FA Cup semi-final]] loss to rivals Chelsea at Wembley Stadium.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39604653 |title=Chelsea 4–2 Tottenham |date=22 April 2017 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=13 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613040448/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39604653 |url-status=live}}</ref> In the last match at White Hart Lane on 14 May, Harry Kane scored the 2–0 goal as Tottenham beat [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] 2–1.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39833969 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 2–1 Manchester United |first=Caroline |last=Chapman |website=BBC Sport |date=14 May 2017 |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=23 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230523105828/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39833969 |url-status=live}}</ref> With two games remaining of the season, Kane stood on 22 goals, two fewer than [[Romelu Lukaku]]. With a combined seven goals in the last two fixtures (a 6–1 win over reigning champions Leicester City<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39879805 |title=Leicester City 1–6 Tottenham Hotspur |first=Tom |last=Rostance |website=BBC Sport |date=18 May 2017 |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=24 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200824151414/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39879805 |url-status=live}}</ref> and a 7–1 win against Hull City<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39912022 |title=Hull City 1–7 Tottenham Hotspur |first=Alex |last=Bysouth |website=BBC Sport |date=21 May 2017 |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=26 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210526110606/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39912022 |url-status=live}}</ref>), Kane finished as the top scorer of the Premier League on 29 goals, and thus won his second consecutive Golden Boot, becoming only the fifth player to do so.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/harry-kane-premier-league-golden-boot-tottenham-hotspur-a7747771.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220509/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/harry-kane-premier-league-golden-boot-tottenham-hotspur-a7747771.html |archive-date=9 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Tottenham striker Harry Kane wins the Premier League's Golden Boot for the second season in a row |first=Luke |last=Brown |newspaper=The Independent |location=London |date=21 May 2017 |access-date=22 May 2017}}</ref>

====2017–2018: Record breaking year====
[[File:Harry Kane (35805453874).jpg|thumb|right|Kane playing for [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] in 2017]]

After failing to find the back of the net in Tottenham's first three games, Kane scored a brace in three of his next four appearances for the club across all competitions.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41133351 |title=Everton 0–3 Tottenham |date=9 September 2017 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=6 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806190158/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41133351 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/sep/14/tottenham-champions-league-borussia-dortmund-harry-kane-wembley |title=Harry Kane's masterclass of craft and energy drags Tottenham to victory |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |first=Barney |last=Ronay |date=14 September 2017 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=5 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210305061118/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/sep/14/tottenham-champions-league-borussia-dortmund-harry-kane-wembley |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2017/09/23/west-ham-vs-tottenham-premier-league-live-score-updates/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2017/09/23/west-ham-vs-tottenham-premier-league-live-score-updates/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=West Ham 2 Tottenham 3: Harry Kane wins battle of the strikers as Mauricio Pochettino declares 'I am in love with him' |first=Matt |last=Law |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |date=23 September 2017 |access-date=2 February 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref> His opening goal against Everton on 9 September was his 100th overall for the club, coming in his 169th appearance.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/us/news/kane-reaches-100-spurs-goals-12-games-fewer-henry-arsenal |title=Kane reaches 100 Spurs goals – in 12 games fewer than Henry for Arsenal |magazine=FourFourTwo |date=9 September 2017 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=28 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128180757/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/us/news/kane-reaches-100-spurs-goals-12-games-fewer-henry-arsenal |url-status=live}}</ref> On 26 September, Kane scored his first [[List of UEFA Champions League hat-tricks|UEFA Champions League hat-trick]] in a 3–0 [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League group stage|group stage]] win against Cypriot champions [[APOEL FC|APOEL]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Hytner |first=David |title=Harry Kane's slick hat-trick smooths Tottenham's path past Apoel Nicosia |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/sep/26/apoel-nicosia-tottenham-champions-league-match-report |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=26 September 2017 |access-date=26 September 2017 |archive-date=2 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210302034005/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/sep/26/apoel-nicosia-tottenham-champions-league-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref> He was awarded Premier League Player of the Month for the fifth time, and named September 2017 – in which he scored 13 goals in 10 club and international games – as the best month of his career.<ref>{{cite news |last=Rosser |first=Jack |title=Harry Kane hails September as his best ever month after Premier League award |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/harry-kane-hails-september-as-his-best-ever-month-after-premier-league-award-a3658471.html |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |date=14 October 2017 |access-date=14 October 2017 |archive-date=29 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210129152921/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/harry-kane-hails-september-as-his-best-ever-month-after-premier-league-award-a3658471.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 23 December 2017, Kane equalled Alan Shearer's record of 36 Premier League goals in a calendar year, having scored a hat-trick in a 0–3 away win to Burnley.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42375899 |title=Kane scores hat-trick as Spurs win at Burnley |website=BBC Sport |date=23 December 2017 |access-date=23 December 2017 |archive-date=18 June 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200618011218/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42375899 |url-status=live}}</ref> He surpassed Shearer's record the following game with another hat-trick in the 5–2 home win against Southampton, ending the year with 39 Premier League goals.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/15122/11185155/harry-kanes-record-breaking-2017-the-stats-you-need-to-know-about-the-tottenham-stars-year |title=Harry Kane's record breaking 2017: The stats you need to know about the Tottenham star's year |first=Peter |last=Smith |website=Sky Sports |date=26 December 2017 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=12 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112014508/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/15122/11185155/harry-kanes-record-breaking-2017-the-stats-you-need-to-know-about-the-tottenham-stars-year |url-status=live}}</ref> The hat-trick, his sixth of the year in the Premier League (eighth in all competitions), also made him the first player in Premier League history to score six hat-tricks in a year.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42360004 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 5–2 Southampton |first=Caroline |last=Chapman |website=BBC Sport |date=26 December 2017 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=13 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200713040658/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42360004 |url-status=live}}</ref> With a total of 56 goals scored in all competitions for the year, he also became Europe's top goalscorer of 2017, breaking the seven-year dominance of [[Lionel Messi]] and [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] as Europe's top goalscorer in a calendar year.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/tottenham-harry-kane-first-player-score-more-goals-lionel-messi-cristiano-ronaldo-decade-a3727096.html |title=Tottenham's Harry Kane the first player to score more goals than Lionel Messi or Cristiano Ronaldo in nearly a decade |first=Alex |last=Young |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |date=26 December 2017 |access-date=26 December 2017 |archive-date=28 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128190200/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/tottenham-harry-kane-first-player-score-more-goals-lionel-messi-cristiano-ronaldo-decade-a3727096.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

In January 2018, he scored twice in the 4–0 home win against Everton, and became Tottenham's top goalscorer in the Premier League era, breaking Teddy Sheringham's record of 97 Premier League goals for the club.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jan/13/tottenham-everton-premier-league-report-harry-kane |title=Tottenham outclass uninspired Everton as Harry Kane reaches new milestone |first=Jacob |last=Steinberg |newspaper=The Observer |location=London |date=13 January 2018 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=1 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501210629/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jan/13/tottenham-everton-premier-league-report-harry-kane |url-status=live}}</ref> On 4 February, Kane scored an added-time penalty to equalise in a 2–2 draw with Liverpool at Anfield for his [[List of footballers with 100 or more Premier League goals|100th Premier League goal]]; he achieved the century of league goals in 141 games, beaten only by Alan Shearer's 124.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/tottenham-star-harry-kane-to-wear-special-boots-against-arsenal-to-mark-100-premier-league-goals-a3763286.html |title=Tottenham star Harry Kane to wear special boots against Arsenal to mark 100 Premier League goals |first=Tom |last=Dutton |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |date=10 February 2018 |access-date=19 June 2018 |archive-date=28 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128150118/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/tottenham-star-harry-kane-to-wear-special-boots-against-arsenal-to-mark-100-premier-league-goals-a3763286.html |url-status=live}}</ref> He was named in the PFA Team of the Year for the fourth consecutive season in April 2018, alongside fellow forwards [[Mohamed Salah]] and Sergio Agüero.<ref name=PFA1718>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43810017 |title=Manchester City players dominate PFA team of the year |website=BBC Sport |date=18 April 2018 |access-date=5 May 2018 |archive-date=18 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210518043233/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43810017 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 8 June, Kane signed a new contract to keep him at the club until 2024.<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane: Tottenham striker signs new contract until 2024 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44416749 |access-date=8 June 2018 |website=BBC Sport |date=8 June 2018 |archive-date=28 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128175358/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44416749 |url-status=live}}</ref>

====2018–2019: UEFA Champions League runner-up====
Kane started the season opener against Newcastle United without scoring, before opening his account against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] the following weekend. In doing so he ended his hoodoo of failing to score a Premier League goal in the month of August.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tottenham Fulham Match Report |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45153221 |access-date=18 August 2018 |website=BBC Sport |date=18 August 2018 |archive-date=18 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210618184318/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45153221 |url-status=live}}</ref> He also scored for the first time at [[Old Trafford]] in the following game as Tottenham won 3–0 in what was only their third away win against Manchester United since 1992, as well as the biggest away win against the club in 46 years.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/08/27/manchester-united-vs-tottenham-premier-league-live-score-latest/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/08/27/manchester-united-vs-tottenham-premier-league-live-score-latest/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Lucas Moura piles misery on Jose Mourinho as Tottenham expose Manchester United's brittle defence |first=Sam |last=Wallace |date=27 August 2018 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=28 August 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://talksport.com/football/415729/manchester-united-tottenham-hotspur-jose-mourinho-harry-kane-lucas-moura/ |title=Manchester United 0–3 Tottenham Hotspur: Visitors end Old Trafford hoodoo in style to pile pressure on Jose Mourinho |first=Sean |last=O'Brien |date=27 August 2018 |publisher=Talksport |access-date=28 August 2018 |archive-date=16 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210316183934/https://talksport.com/football/415729/manchester-united-tottenham-hotspur-jose-mourinho-harry-kane-lucas-moura/ |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored the opening goal against [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] on 1 January 2019, and with that goal, he became the first player to have scored a goal against every Premier League team he has faced.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/tottenham/harry-kane-premier-league-goal-record-28-times-the-tottenham-striker-has-hit-the-net-a4028761.html |title=Harry Kane's Premier League goal record: The Tottenham star's best strikes from remarkable 28 team tally |first=Tony |last=Mogan |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |date=2 February 2018 |access-date=5 January 2019 |archive-date=6 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806190127/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/tottenham/harry-kane-premier-league-goal-record-28-times-the-tottenham-striker-has-hit-the-net-a4028761.html |url-status=live}}</ref> On 13 January 2019, against Manchester United at Wembley Stadium, Kane injured his ankle ligament late in the game, thereby missing crucial matches including the [[2018–19 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] round of 16 home game.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46884787 |title=Harry Kane: Tottenham striker out until March with ankle injury |website=BBC Sport |date=15 January 2019 |access-date=15 January 2019 |archive-date=8 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108002929/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46884787 |url-status=live}}</ref>

He returned to the first team squad on 23 February 2019, in a match against Burnley, and was immediately placed in the starting eleven. He scored the equalising goal in the 65th minute to tie the score 1–1, although the match ended a 2–1 defeat.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47262464 |title=Burnley 2–1 Tottenham |website=BBC Sport |access-date=27 February 2019 |archive-date=6 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806190150/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47262464 |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane scored the only goal in the Champions League round of 16 [[Signal Iduna Park|away]] tie against [[Borussia Dortmund]] to ensure a 4–0 win on aggregate and progress to the club's second quarter-final in the Champions League. The goal also made him the [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C. in European football|club's top goalscorer in European competitions]] with 24 goals scored.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/dortmund-vs-tottenham-result-harry-kane-goal-watch-video-highlights-replay-five-things-learned-a8809311.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220509/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/dortmund-vs-tottenham-result-harry-kane-goal-watch-video-highlights-replay-five-things-learned-a8809311.html |archive-date=9 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Dortmund vs Tottenham result: Five things we learned as Harry Kane goal send Spurs to quarter-finals |first=Luke |last=Brown |date=5 March 2019 |newspaper=The Independent}}</ref> During the first leg of the quarter-final in the Champions League on 9 April 2019 against Manchester City, he again suffered an ankle injury, which ended his season domestically in the [[2018–19 Premier League|Premier League]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2019/04/10/harry-kane-fearing-worst-ankle-injury-desperate-fit-englands/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2019/04/10/harry-kane-fearing-worst-ankle-injury-desperate-fit-englands/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Harry Kane fearing worst over ankle injury but is desperate to be fit for England's Nations League campaign |first=Matt |last=Law |date=10 April 2019 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph}}{{cbignore}}</ref> He did, however, return for the [[2019 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]] on 1 June, although his selection after his injury became a subject of debate as Tottenham lost 2–0 to Liverpool.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2019/06/01/harry-kane-gamble-backfires-tottenham-striker-not-alone-wilting/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2019/06/01/harry-kane-gamble-backfires-tottenham-striker-not-alone-wilting/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Harry Kane gamble backfires for Tottenham but striker not alone in wilting in Madrid heat |first=Jason |last=Burt |date=1 June 2019 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/champions-league-final-liverpool-tottenham-madrid-harry-kane-injury-latest-a8940371.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220509/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/champions-league-final-liverpool-tottenham-madrid-harry-kane-injury-latest-a8940371.html |archive-date=9 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Champions League final: Why the decision to start Harry Kane ultimately proved irrelevant for Tottenham |first=Miguel |last=Delaney |date=2 June 2019 |newspaper=The Independent}}</ref>

====2019–2020: Injury struggles====
Kane started Tottenham's first game of the [[2019–20 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|2019–20 season]], scoring twice in a 3–1 home win against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]]. Kane's first goal of the game was his first at the [[Tottenham Hotspur Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49215981 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 3:1 Aston Villa |first=Neil |last=Johnston |website=BBC Sport |date=10 August 2019 |access-date=10 August 2019 |archive-date=20 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120021510/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49215981 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 1 January 2020, in a 1–0 defeat to Southampton at [[St Mary's Stadium]], Kane suffered a hamstring injury.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/11899157/harry-kane-suffers-hamstring-injury |title=Harry Kane suffers hamstring injury in Tottenham's defeat at Southampton |website=Sky Sports |date=1 January 2020 |access-date=9 January 2020 |archive-date=6 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806190129/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/11899157/harry-kane-suffers-hamstring-injury |url-status=live}}</ref> The damage to his hamstring required an operation which would see him out of action for a few months.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/jan/09/harry-kane-needs-surgery-out-until-april-tottenham-hamstring-euro-2020 |title=Harry Kane needs surgery and is out until April, Tottenham confirm |first=David |last=Hytner |date=9 January 2020 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=9 January 2020 |archive-date=26 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210526082812/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/jan/09/harry-kane-needs-surgery-out-until-april-tottenham-hamstring-euro-2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> Due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]] which resulted in the suspension of League matches, he did not play any further matches until 19 June.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53096323 |title=Tottenham v Man Utd: Harry Kane, Son Heung-min & Moussa Sissoko to start |date=18 June 2020 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=24 June 2020 |archive-date=4 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204100904/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53096323 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 23 June, in his 200th Premier League appearance for Tottenham, he scored his first goal of 2020 against West Ham, sealing a 2–0 win.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/jun/24/harry-kane-fundamental-to-tottenham-says-mourinho-after-west-ham-win |title=José Mourinho hails 'fundamental' Harry Kane as Moyes hits out at VAR |first=Louise |last=Taylor |date=24 June 2020 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=24 June 2020 |archive-date=30 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210630185048/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/jun/24/harry-kane-fundamental-to-tottenham-says-mourinho-after-west-ham-win |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53159676 |title=Harry Kane: 'I want to reach 200 Premier League goals' |date=23 June 2020 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=24 June 2020 |archive-date=14 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114132155/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53159676 |url-status=live}}</ref>

====2020–2021: Third Golden Boot and Playmaker of the Season====
[[File:NŠ Mura Tottenham Hotspur 3.jpg|thumb|266x266px|Kane playing for [[Tottenham Hotspur]] in 2021]]

Kane scored his first goal of the season in the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] match against [[PFC Lokomotiv Plovdiv|Lokomotiv Plovdiv]], helping the team to win 2–1 after Plovdiv had two players sent off late in the second half.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54181461 |title=Lokomotiv Plovdiv 1–2 Tottenham Hotspur |website=BBC Sport |date=17 September 2020 |access-date=20 September 2020 |archive-date=28 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128000413/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54181461 |url-status=live}}</ref> His first league goal of the [[2020–21 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|2020–21 season]] came in the second league match following a spree of four goals which were all scored by [[Son Heung-min]] and assisted by Kane, giving Spurs a 5–2 win over Southampton. This is the first time in Premier League history a player has provided four assists to the same teammate in a match and Kane became just the sixth player in Premier League history to assist four goals in a single match, and the first English player to do so.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54135440 |title=Southampton 2–5 Tottenham Hotspur |first=Gary |last=Rose |website=BBC Sport |date=20 September 2020 |access-date=20 September 2020 |archive-date=20 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200920142611/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54135440 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Kane scored a [[List of UEFA Europa League hat-tricks|hat-trick]] against [[Maccabi Haifa F.C.|Maccabi Haifa]] in the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round#Play-off round|UEFA Europa League play-off]] round on 1 October, securing qualification for the group stage.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/mourinho-kane-scores-so-many-hat-tricks-he-probably-doesnt/m2sfm7itn8s11msaxtugy2hu7 |title=Mourinho: Kane scores so many hat-tricks he probably doesn't keep the balls anymore! |website=Goal |date=2 October 2020 |access-date=4 October 2020 |archive-date=10 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201010002831/https://www.goal.com/en/news/mourinho-kane-scores-so-many-hat-tricks-he-probably-doesnt/m2sfm7itn8s11msaxtugy2hu7 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 4 October, he scored a brace in a 6–1 away win against Manchester United, which is the biggest win for Tottenham at Old Trafford and their best result against United since a home win in 1932.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/oct/04/manchester-united-tottenham-premier-league-match-report |title=Harry Kane stars in Tottenham's 6–1 thrashing of hapless Manchester United |website=The Guardian |date=4 October 2020 |access-date=4 October 2020 |archive-date=18 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210618133623/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/oct/04/manchester-united-tottenham-premier-league-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54313274 |title=Manchester United 1 : 6 Tottenham Hotspur |website=BBC Sport |access-date=5 October 2020 |archive-date=7 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201007181614/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54313274 |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his 200th goal for Tottenham in his 300th appearance for the club in the 3–1 win over [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]] in the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League group stage|group stage]] of the Europa League.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/nov/05/ludogorets-tottenham-europa-league-match-report |title=Harry Kane makes it 200 goals in 300 Spurs games during win at Ludogorets |first=Louise |last=Taylor |date=5 November 2020 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=5 November 2020 |archive-date=25 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125023811/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/nov/05/ludogorets-tottenham-europa-league-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane scored in Tottenham's 2–0 victory over rivals Arsenal making him the record highest goalscorer in the history of the North London Derby with 11 goals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55118788 |title=Tottenham 2–0 Arsenal |first=Phil |last=McNulty |date=6 December 2020 |website=BBC Sport|access-date=6 December 2020|archive-date=22 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122131718/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55118788|url-status=live}}</ref> It was also Kane's 100th home goal for Tottenham in all competitions, and his 250th career goal for club and country.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportsmax.tv/index.php/other-sports/item/74455-tottenham-2-0-arsenal-kane-and-son-seal-north-london-bragging-rights-to-send-spurs-top |title=Tottenham 2–0 Arsenal: Kane and Son seal north London bragging rights to send Spurs top |website=Sports Max |date=6 December 2020|access-date=7 December 2020|archive-date=17 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210517194902/https://www.sportsmax.tv/index.php/other-sports/item/74455-tottenham-2-0-arsenal-kane-and-son-seal-north-london-bragging-rights-to-send-spurs-top|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 2 January 2021, Kane converted a penalty to open the scoring and later provided an assist during Tottenham's 3–0 home victory over [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]. This brought both Kane's goal and assist tally in the league to 10, making him the first player in [[Big Five (association football)|Europe's top five leagues]] to reach double digits for goals and assists in the 2020–21 season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 January 2021 |title=Kane and Son still have Tottenham believing anything is possible |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/english-premier-league/story/4277772/kane-and-son-still-have-tottenham-believing-anything-is-possible-after-duo-star-vs-leeds|access-date=2 January 2021 |publisher=ESPN|archive-date=22 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122015214/https://www.espn.com/soccer/english-premier-league/story/4277772/kane-and-son-still-have-tottenham-believing-anything-is-possible-after-duo-star-vs-leeds|url-status=live}}</ref> On 7 March, he scored a brace against Crystal Palace in a 4–1 win; the last goal was assisted by Son Heung-min, and this, their 14th combined goal effort whereby one assisted another, set a record for the most goal combinations in a Premier League season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/tottenham-hotspur/story/4257853/tottenhams-kane-and-son-break-goalscoring-record-in-premier-league |title=Tottenham's Kane and Son break goalscoring record in Premier League |date=7 March 2021 |publisher=ESPN |access-date=8 March 2021 |archive-date=4 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210504051342/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/tottenham-hotspur/story/4257853/tottenhams-kane-and-son-break-goalscoring-record-in-premier-league |url-status=live}}</ref> On 23 May, he scored a goal in a 4–2 win over Leicester City, to reach his 23rd goal of the season and to win the third Golden Boot award in his career.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11675/12315126/harry-kane-tottenham-striker-wins-premier-league-golden-boot-award-for-third-time |title=Harry Kane: Tottenham striker wins Premier League Golden Boot award for third time |website=Sky Sports |date=23 May 202 |access-date=23 May 2021 |archive-date=23 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210523205458/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11675/12315126/harry-kane-tottenham-striker-wins-premier-league-golden-boot-award-for-third-time |url-status=live}}</ref> He also won the [[Premier League Playmaker of the Season]] award for most assists in a season, becoming the first player to win both the Golden Boot and Playmaker awards in the same season since the introduction of the [[playmaker]]s' award in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/2154211 |title=Kane wins double with Golden Boot and Playmaker awards |date=23 May 2021 |publisher=Premier League |access-date=27 May 2021 |archive-date=31 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531045805/https://www.premierleague.com/news/2154211 |url-status=live}}</ref>

====2021–2022: Desire to leave Tottenham====
[[File:Manchester United v Tottenham Hotspur, 12 March 2022 (24).jpg|thumb|Kane (10) playing for [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] in 2022]]

The [[2021–22 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|2021–22 season]] was preceded by a dispute over a desire by Kane to leave Tottenham, saying he had a [[gentlemen's agreement]] with chairman [[Daniel Levy (businessman)|Daniel Levy]] that would allow him to leave in the summer.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/harry-kane-tottenham-transfer-gentleman-s-agreement-b935786.html |title=Harry Kane hoping 'gentleman's agreement' will allow him to leave this summer |date=18 May 2021 |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |first=Dan |last=Kilpatrick |access-date=28 August 2021 |archive-date=28 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828121243/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/harry-kane-tottenham-transfer-gentleman-s-agreement-b935786.html |url-status=live}}</ref> The agreement was not honoured, and Levy rejected the interest expressed by Manchester City for Kane's services,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2021/08/19/daniel-levy-playing-hardball-leaves-harry-kane-stuck-should/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2021/08/19/daniel-levy-playing-hardball-leaves-harry-kane-stuck-should/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Daniel Levy playing hardball leaves Harry Kane stuck but he should not be vilified |first=Jason |last=Burt |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |date=19 August 2021}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/aug/25/harry-kane-finds-out-the-hard-way-daniel-levy-is-not-for-turning |title=Harry Kane finds out the hard way Daniel Levy is not for turning |first=Ed |last=Aarons |date=25 August 2021 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=28 August 2021 |archive-date=28 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828121243/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/aug/25/harry-kane-finds-out-the-hard-way-daniel-levy-is-not-for-turning |url-status=live}}</ref> including a £127&nbsp;million transfer bid.<ref>{{Cite news |date=26 August 2021 |title=Harry Kane confirms he is staying at Spurs after accepting City deal is dead |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/aug/25/harry-kane-confirms-he-will-be-staying-at-tottenham-this-summer-manchester-city|access-date=20 February 2022 |newspaper=The Guardian |archive-date=20 February 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220220055025/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/aug/25/harry-kane-confirms-he-will-be-staying-at-tottenham-this-summer-manchester-city|url-status=live}}</ref> Kane failed to turn up for pre-season training and did not play the first two games of the season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58133102 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 1–0 Manchester City |website=BBC Sport |date=15 August 2021 |first=Phil |last=McNulty|access-date=28 August 2021|archive-date=27 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210827034635/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58133102|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4202406/2021/08/18/harry-kane-has-not-travelled-for-tottenhams-game-against-pacos-de-ferreira/ |title=Harry Kane has not travelled for Tottenham's game against Pacos de Ferreira |first=Charlie |last=Eccleshare |website=The Athletic |date=18 August 2021 |access-date=28 August 2021 |archive-date=28 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828121247/https://theathletic.com/news/harry-kane-will-not-be-involved-for-tottenham-against-pacos-de-ferreira/thGyEzRY6Fyp |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his season bow on 22 August as a substitute against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] – his first appearance since returning late for pre-season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/aug/22/nuno-espirito-santo-praises-harry-kane-for-helping-tottenham-to-win-at-wolves |title=Nuno Espírito Santo praises Harry Kane for helping Tottenham to win at Wolves |first=Paul |last=Doyle |date=22 August 2021 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=28 August 2021 |archive-date=28 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828121247/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/aug/22/nuno-espirito-santo-praises-harry-kane-for-helping-tottenham-to-win-at-wolves |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane announced his desire to stay at Tottenham on 25 August after the move to Manchester City failed to materialise, with Kane stating: "I will be staying at Tottenham this summer and will be 100 per cent focused on helping the team achieve success."<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane announces he is to stay at Tottenham |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11675/12390231/harry-kane-announces-he-is-to-stay-at-tottenham-this-summer-after-failed-man-city-bids |date=26 August 2021 |website=Sky Sports}}{{cbignore}}</ref> The following day Kane made his first appearance in the [[UEFA Europa Conference League]], against [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Paços de Ferreira]]. He scored twice in a 3–0 win to secure the team's progress to the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa Conference League group stage|group stage]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58333505 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 3–0 Paços de Ferreira |date=27 August 2021 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=28 August 2021 |archive-date=28 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828124621/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58333505 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 30 September, in the second match of the group stage, he scored a hat-trick in 20 minutes against [[NŠ Mura|Mura]] after coming on as a substitute to win 5–1.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/sep/30/tottenham-mura-europa-conference-league-match-report |title=Harry Kane's 20-minute hat-trick sinks Mura and drags Spurs from their rut |first=Nick |last=Ames |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=3 October 2021 |archive-date=3 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211003135655/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/sep/30/tottenham-mura-europa-conference-league-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref> This was the first hat-trick ever scored in the [[Europa Conference League]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaconferenceleague/news/026d-135e7f17c89d-8320608169af-1000--europa-conference-league-round-up-kane-trebles-up-roma-sail-on/ |title=Europa Conference League round-up: Kane trebles up, Roma sail on |date=30 September 2021 |publisher=UEFA |access-date=8 October 2022 |archive-date=8 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221008234709/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaconferenceleague/news/026d-135e7f17c89d-8320608169af-1000--europa-conference-league-round-up-kane-trebles-up-roma-sail-on/ |url-status=live}}</ref> and made Kane the first player to score a hat-trick in all three current major UEFA club competitions (the Champions League, Europa League, and Europa Conference League).

On 17 October 2021, Kane scored his first Premier League goal of the season in a 3–2 away win against [[Newcastle United]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/newcastle-vs-tottenham-result-premier-league-2021-harry-kane-owners-b960946.html |title=Newcastle 2–3 Tottenham:Harry Kane nets first league goal of season to help spoil Toon party |date=18 October 2021 |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |access-date=18 October 2021|archive-date=18 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211018130932/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/newcastle-vs-tottenham-result-premier-league-2021-harry-kane-owners-b960946.html|url-status=live}}</ref> His second goal of the season came on 19 December, when he scored the opener in a 2–2 home draw against Liverpool.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/dec/19/tottenham-liverpool-premier-league-match-report |title=Son earns Tottenham point in thrilling draw with 10-man Liverpool |first=David |last=Hytner |date=19 December 2021 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=20 December 2021 |archive-date=20 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211220211541/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/dec/19/tottenham-liverpool-premier-league-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 February 2022, Kane scored twice, including a 95th-minute winner, in a thrilling 3–2 victory over Manchester City.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Man City 2–3 Tottenham: Harry Kane gives Spurs stunning late win over Premier League leaders |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60357463 |website=BBC Sport |date=19 February 2022|access-date=5 November 2022|archive-date=5 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221105124452/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60357463|url-status=live}}</ref> This ended City's 15-game unbeaten streak in the league. On 26 February, Kane scored against Leeds United, and assisted Son; the assist was the 37th time Kane and Son had combined to score, setting a new record of goal-scoring partnerships in the Premier League.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/blog-the-toe-poke/story/4256582/tottenhams-harry-kaneson-heung-min-become-premier-leagues-all-time-top-scoring-partnership |title=Tottenham's Harry Kane, Son Heung-Min become Premier League's all-time top scoring partnership |publisher=ESPN |date=26 February 2022 |access-date=26 February 2022 |archive-date=26 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220226172113/https://www.espn.com/soccer/blog-the-toe-poke/story/4256582/tottenhams-harry-kaneson-heung-min-become-premier-leagues-all-time-top-scoring-partnership |url-status=live}}</ref> On 16 March, Kane scored in a 2–0 win away at Brighton, bringing his Premier League away goal tally to 95, surpassing [[Wayne Rooney]]'s record for most Premier League goals scored away from home.<ref name="sportingNewsGoals">{{cite web |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/harry-kane-most-premier-league-away-goals-who-has-history-new-english-record/ny9qarzot78wo6i7mwosuqfg |title=Who has the most away goals in Premier League history? Harry Kane sets new English top flight record |date=17 March 2022 |publisher=Sporting News|access-date=25 May 2022|archive-date=25 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220525134141/https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/harry-kane-most-premier-league-away-goals-who-has-history-new-english-record/ny9qarzot78wo6i7mwosuqfg|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2022–2023: All-time Tottenham top goalscorer and final season====
Kane scored his first goal of the season in the [[Chelsea F.C.–Tottenham Hotspur F.C. rivalry|London derby]] away at Chelsea, rescuing a point for Tottenham by scoring in the sixth minute of injury time to bring the score to 2–2.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/aug/14/chelsea-tottenham-hotspur-premier-league-match-report |title=Kane snatches draw for Spurs at Chelsea as clashing Conte and Tuchel see red |first=Nick |last=Ames |newspaper=The Guardian |date=14 August 2022 |access-date=14 August 2022 |archive-date=14 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220814202138/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/aug/14/chelsea-tottenham-hotspur-premier-league-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref> This took his tally of Premier League goals scored for Tottenham to 184, equalling Sergio Agüero's record of most goals scored for a single Premier League club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.101greatgoals.com/news/harry-kane-equals-sergio-agueros-all-time-premier-league-record-with-strike-vs-chelsea/ |title=Harry Kane equals Sergio Aguero's all-time Premier League record with strike vs Chelsea |first=Conor |last=Laird |website=101 Great Goals |date=14 August 2022 |access-date=14 August 2022 |archive-date=26 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220826143413/https://www.101greatgoals.com/news/harry-kane-equals-sergio-agueros-all-time-premier-league-record-with-strike-vs-chelsea/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane broke the record the following game when he scored the only goal in the game against Wolverhampton Wanderers, becoming the first player to score 185 goals in the Premier League for a single club.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.itv.com/news/2022-08-20/tottenham-vs-wolves-harry-kane-breaks-premier-league-score-record-in-1-0-win |title=Tottenham vs Wolves: Harry Kane breaks Premier League goal record in 1–0 win |website=ITV News |date=20 August 2022 |access-date=20 August 2022 |archive-date=9 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230409065852/https://www.itv.com/news/2022-08-20/tottenham-vs-wolves-harry-kane-breaks-premier-league-score-record-in-1-0-win |url-status=live}}</ref> On 5 February 2023, Tottenham stated that Kane had become their all-time top scorer, overtaking [[Jimmy Greaves]] with his 267th goal for Tottenham and 200th in the Premier League, in a 1–0 home victory against Manchester City.<ref>{{Cite web |date=5 February 2023 |title=Kane passes Greaves as Spurs' all-time top scorer |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64532175 |access-date=5 February 2023 |website=BBC Sport |archive-date=9 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230409070942/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64532175 |url-status=live}}</ref> This fact was disputed, however, as Tottenham do not count the two goals Greaves scored in the [[1962 FA Charity Shield]], which would put him on 268.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://talksport.com/football/1312808/harry-kane-jimmy-greaves-tottenham-all-time-goalscoring-record-stats/ |title=Stats prove Kane has not actually equalled Greaves' all-time Tottenham goalscoring record |date=24 January 2023 |website=talkSPORT|access-date=6 February 2023|archive-date=30 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231030225434/https://talksport.com/football/1312808/harry-kane-jimmy-greaves-tottenham-all-time-goalscoring-record-stats/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/12782897/harry-kane-tottenham-striker-could-hit-200-premier-league-goals-against-arsenal-and-break-jimmy-greaves-goal-record |title=Harry Kane: Tottenham striker could hit 200 Premier League goals against Arsenal and break Jimmy Greaves' goal record |website=Sky Sports|access-date=6 February 2023|archive-date=20 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230120162009/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/12782897/harry-kane-tottenham-striker-could-hit-200-premier-league-goals-against-arsenal-and-break-jimmy-greaves-goal-record|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.msn.com/en-gb/sport/football/tottenham-refuse-to-budge-on-harry-kane-matching-their-scoring-record/ar-AA16JIqG |title=MSN: "Tottenham REFUSE to budge on Harry Kane matching their scoring record" |publisher=MSN |access-date=6 February 2023 |archive-date=9 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230409202342/https://www.msn.com/en-gb/sport/football/tottenham-refuse-to-budge-on-harry-kane-matching-their-scoring-record/ar-AA16JIqG |url-status=live}}</ref> On 11 March 2023, Kane scored his 269th and 270th goals with a brace in a 3–1 victory against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] giving him the now undisputed record.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kane double helps Tottenham lift gloom with win over Forest |url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/kane-double-helps-tottenham-lift-gloom-with-win-over-forest-2023-03-11/ |work=Reuters |first=Martyn |last=Herman |date=11 March 2023 |access-date=11 March 2023 |archive-date=11 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230311191419/https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/kane-double-helps-tottenham-lift-gloom-with-win-over-forest-2023-03-11/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2023, he finished second to [[Erling Haaland]], with 30 goals, becoming the first player to score 30 times in two separate 38-game Premier League seasons.<ref>{{cite web |title=How Harry Kane Keeps Getting Better in a Tottenham Team That is Getting Worse |url=https://theanalyst.com/eu/2023/05/how-harry-kane-keeps-getting-better-in-a-tottenham-team-that-is-getting-worse/ |publisher=Opta Analyst |date=28 May 2023 |access-date=28 May 2023 |archive-date=28 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230528182629/https://theanalyst.com/eu/2023/05/how-harry-kane-keeps-getting-better-in-a-tottenham-team-that-is-getting-worse/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Following the departure of [[Karim Benzema]] from [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] on 6 June 2023, manager [[Carlo Ancelotti]], who was interested in signing Kane, reportedly asked his board to initiate a possible transfer.<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane: Real Madrid want Tottenham striker to replace Karim Benzema |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/65808462 |website=BBC Sport |date=5 June 2023 |access-date= 5 June 2023 |archive-date= 5 June 2023 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20230605095105/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/65808462 |url-status= live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Transfer news: Spurs to resist Kane approach |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/articles/c4n4l0x8pvlo |website=BBC Sport |date=30 May 2023 |access-date= 5 June 2023 |archive-date= 5 June 2023 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20230605192835/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/articles/c4n4l0x8pvlo |url-status= live}}</ref> In late June 2023, [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] made an initial bid for Kane of £70&nbsp;million with one year left in his contract, which was rejected.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66030410 |title=Bayern set to make improved offer for Kane |website=BBC Sport |date=28 June 2023|access-date=11 August 2023|archive-date=16 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230716163929/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66030410|url-status=live}}</ref> In July, he was included in Tottenham's squad for their pre-season tour,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66200867 |title=Kane in Spurs tour squad but Lloris left out |website=BBC Sport|access-date=11 August 2023|archive-date=18 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718184733/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66200867|url-status=live}}</ref> with Bayern Munich honorary president [[Uli Hoeneß]] saying that there had been talks between the club and the player's advisors, stating that Kane had "clearly signalled in all conversations" that he wished to transfer to Bayern Munich.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66105654 |title=Bayern's Hoeness confident of Kane deal |website=BBC Sport|access-date=19 August 2023|archive-date=20 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230720094306/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66105654|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66284840 |title=Harry Kane: Top European clubs holding out for Tottenham striker |website=BBC Sport |access-date= 19 August 2023 |archive-date= 24 July 2023 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20230724115856/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66284840 |url-status= live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66200867 |title=Kane in Spurs tour squad but Lloris left out |website=BBC Sport |date=14 July 2023|access-date=11 August 2023|archive-date=18 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718184733/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66200867|url-status=live}}</ref> On 6 August, Kane scored four goals as Tottenham beat [[Shakhtar Donetsk]] 5–1 in their penultimate pre-season friendly before the start of the Premier League.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66422649 |title=Harry Kane scores four as Tottenham beat Shakhtar; Harry Maguire booed as Manchester United draw |website=BBC Sport |access-date= 11 August 2023 |archive-date= 20 September 2023 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20230920200737/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66422649 |url-status= live}}</ref> On the next day, Tottenham rejected another bid from Bayern Munich,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66431705 |title=Harry Kane: Tottenham reject latest Bayern Munich offer for England captain |website=BBC Sport |date=7 August 2023|access-date=12 August 2023|archive-date=12 August 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230812152239/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66431705|url-status=live}}</ref> for a reported fee of £86&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/07/tottenham-reject-86m-harry-kane-bid-from-bayern-munich |title=Tottenham reject £86m Harry Kane bid from Bayern Munich |website=The Guardian |date=7 August 2023 |access-date=24 August 2023 |archive-date=24 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230824105331/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/07/tottenham-reject-86m-harry-kane-bid-from-bayern-munich |url-status=live}}</ref> On 10 August, it was reported that Bayern Munich and Tottenham had agreed a deal in principle for Kane which was worth more than €100&nbsp;million (£86.4m).<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane transfer news: Bayern Munich agree deal in principle with Tottenham for striker |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66412269 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=10 August 2023 |archive-date=26 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230926162424/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66412269 |url-status=live}}</ref> His departure was later confirmed by manager [[Ange Postecoglou]] via press conference.<ref>{{Citation |title=ANGE POSTECOGLOU'S FIRST PREMIER LEAGUE PRESS CONFERENCE // BRENTFORD V TOTTENHAM HOTSPUR | date=11 August 2023 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D8erT_cG0Do |access-date=11 August 2023 |archive-date=11 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230811151328/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D8erT_cG0Do&gl=US&hl=en |url-status=live}}</ref> The same day, it was reported that Kane was to undergo a medical at Bayern Munich after being given permission to travel to Germany by Tottenham.<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane: Tottenham and England striker to have medical at Bayern Munich |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66276899 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=10 August 2023 |archive-date=11 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230811080454/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66276899 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 12 August, Kane posted a farewell video on [[Instagram]], thanking Tottenham staff and supporters for his time at the club.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Harry Kane on Instagram: "Hard to put into words how to say goodbye to a club and fans who have done so much for me in my career. You will always be in my heart. Thank you Tottenham, thank you Tottenham fans. 💙" |url=https://www.instagram.com/reel/Cv1h7E8N6lj/ |access-date=12 August 2023 |website=Instagram |archive-date=12 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230812074643/https://www.instagram.com/reel/Cv1h7E8N6lj/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Tottenham released an official statement shortly after thanking Kane for his service.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Harry Kane departs to Bayern Munich |date=12 August 2023 |url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2023/august/harry-kane-departs-to-bayern-munich/ |access-date=12 August 2023 |publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C. |archive-date=12 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230812080328/https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2023/august/harry-kane-departs-to-bayern-munich/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Tottenham chairman [[Daniel Levy (businessman)|Daniel Levy]] also mentioned that Kane wanted a new challenge and decided not to sign a new contract with the club.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/cpdjgk2jej5o |title=Levy says Kane was 'clear he wanted a fresh challenge' |website=BBC Sport |date=12 August 2023|access-date=12 August 2023|archive-date=12 August 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230812152241/https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/cpdjgk2jej5o|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Bayern Munich===
====2023–2024: Debut season and first European Golden Shoe====
After Bayern Munich and Tottenham agreed on a deal on 10 August 2023, Kane agreed personal terms and flew to [[Munich]] the next day.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.sky.com/story/harry-kane-tottenham-striker-arrives-in-germany-to-finalise-move-to-bayern-munich-12938261 |title=Harry Kane: Tottenham striker arrives in Germany to finalise move to Bayern Munich |website=Sky News |date=11 August 2023 |access-date=12 August 2023 |archive-date=12 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230812152805/https://news.sky.com/story/harry-kane-tottenham-striker-arrives-in-germany-to-finalise-move-to-bayern-munich-12938261 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 12 August, Bayern Munich announced the signing of Kane on a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 August 2023 |title=FC Bayern sign Harry Kane |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/08/move-from-the-premier-league-fc-bayern-sign-harry-kane |access-date=12 August 2023 |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |archive-date=12 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230812081609/https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/08/move-from-the-premier-league-fc-bayern-sign-harry-kane |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=12 August 2023 |title=Bayern Munich sign England striker Harry Kane from Tottenham Hotspur |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/harry-kane-joins-bayern-munich-tottenham-hotspur-england-striker-23904 |access-date=12 August 2023 |publisher=Bundesliga |archive-date=12 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230812122744/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/harry-kane-joins-bayern-munich-tottenham-hotspur-england-striker-23904 |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane became the [[List of most expensive association football transfers|most expensive signing]] in Bundesliga history, costing €100 million plus €10 million bonuses in transfer fees, surpassing the €80 million transfer fee paid by Bayern Munich for [[Lucas Hernandez]] in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bayern Munich sign Lucas Hernandez from Atletico Madrid for club-record fee |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11890/11676677/bayern-munich-sign-lucas-hernandez-from-atletico-madrid-for-club-record-fee |date=27 March 2019 |access-date=12 August 2023 |publisher=Sky Sports |archive-date=2 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230402004415/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11890/11676677/bayern-munich-sign-lucas-hernandez-from-atletico-madrid-for-club-record-fee |url-status=live}}</ref>{{citation needed|date=April 2026}}

He made his debut for Bayern on the same day he joined the club, as a 64th-minute substitute in a 3–0 defeat to [[RB Leipzig]] in the [[2023 DFL-Supercup]].<ref name="DFL">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66489307 |title=Harry Kane makes Bayern Munich debut in German Super Cup defeat by RB Leipzig |website=BBC Sport |date=12 August 2023 |access-date=12 August 2023 |archive-date=12 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230812205621/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66489307 |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on the opening day of the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|2023–24 Bundesliga season]], also providing the assist for [[Leroy Sané]]'s early opener, as Bayern won 4–0 away to [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Sutcliffe |first=Steve |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66551395 |title=Werder Bremen 0–4 Bayern Munich: Harry Kane scores and assists on Bundesliga debut |website=BBC Sport |date=18 August 2023 |access-date=18 August 2023 |archive-date=18 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230818205116/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66551395 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 27 August, Kane netted his first Bayern brace in a 3–1 home league victory against [[FC Augsburg]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Rostance |first=Tom |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66635289 |title=Harry Kane: England captain scores twice as Bayern Munich beat Augsburg |website=BBC Sport |date=27 August 2023 |access-date=27 August 2023 |archive-date=27 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827180140/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66635289 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 15 September, Kane scored his 300th career club goal as Bayern's home league match against [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] ended in a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66822863 |title=Bayern Munich 2–2 Bayer Leverkusen: Harry Kane scores again in thrilling draw |website=BBC Sport |date=15 September 2023 |access-date=15 September 2023 |archive-date=15 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230915220037/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66822863 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 20 September, he scored his first [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] goal for Bayern on his European debut, converting a penalty in a 4–3 win over Manchester United.<ref>{{cite web |last=Dawkes |first=Phil |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66861399 |title=Bayern Munich 4–3 Manchester United: Harry Kane on target as Red Devils poor form continues |website=BBC Sport |date=20 September 2023 |access-date=20 September 2023 |archive-date=3 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231003114006/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66861399 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 23 September, Kane got his first hat-trick for Bayern as well as two assists in a 7–0 victory against [[VfL Bochum]], taking his league goal tally to seven and setting a new club record for most goals by a player in his first five Bundesliga appearances.<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 September 2023 |title='Super Bayern' in seventh heaven with Kane |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/09/super-bayern-on-winning-streak-with-kane |access-date=30 September 2023 |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |archive-date=3 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231003212922/https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/09/super-bayern-on-winning-streak-with-kane |url-status=live}}</ref> The hat-trick was also his first domestic league triple since December 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66902025 |title=Bayern Munich 7–0 VfL Bochum: Kane scores hat-trick and assists twice in thrashing |website=BBC Sport |date=20 September 2023 |access-date=28 September 2023 |archive-date=28 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230928010243/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66902025 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 October, Kane scored a second-half hat-trick and got an assist in an 8–0 victory over [[SV Darmstadt 98|Darmstadt 98]], including a goal from inside his own half.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67249631 |title=Bayern Munich 8–0 Darmstadt 98 |website=BBC Sport |date=28 October 2023 |access-date=28 October 2023 |archive-date=28 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231028160107/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67249631 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 4 November 2023, Kane scored his third and back-to-back hat-trick of the season on his [[Der Klassiker]] debut, which ended in a 4–0 away win against [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Mills |first=Richard |url=https://www.goal.com/en-cm/news/harry-kane-destroys-dortmund-bayern-hat-trick-klassiker-debut-leroy-sane-unstoppable-champions-dominant-win/blt9eb1f42116c2707e |title=Harry Kane destroys Dortmund! Bayern striker grabs hat-trick on Klassiker debut and Leroy Sane is unstoppable as champions enjoy dominant win |website=Goal |date=4 November 2023 |access-date=4 November 2023 |archive-date=18 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231118021416/https://www.goal.com/en-cm/news/harry-kane-destroys-dortmund-bayern-hat-trick-klassiker-debut-leroy-sane-unstoppable-champions-dominant-win/blt9eb1f42116c2707e |url-status=live }}</ref> With 20 goal participations and 15 goals in 10 games he broke three Bundesliga records, and matched [[Gerd Müller]]'s record from the [[1968–69 Bundesliga|1968–69 Bundesliga season]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kane stellt vier Bundesliga-Rekorde auf einmal auf |url=https://www.kicker.de/kane-stellt-vier-bundesliga-rekorde-auf-einmal-auf-977533/artikel |date=5 November 2023 |access-date=5 November 2023 |website=kicker |language=de-DE |archive-date=11 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231111065128/https://www.kicker.de/kane-stellt-vier-bundesliga-rekorde-auf-einmal-auf-977533/artikel |url-status=live }}</ref> Four days later, he netted a double in a 2–1 victory against [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]], which secured his club's qualification to the Champions League knockout stages on top of their group.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayern-munich-galatasaray-live-champions-league-teams-stats-icardi-kane-25252 |title=Harry Kane double sends Bayern Munich through to UEFA Champions League last 16 |website=Bundesliga |date=8 November 2023 |access-date=22 November 2023 |archive-date=22 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231122045846/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayern-munich-galatasaray-live-champions-league-teams-stats-icardi-kane-25252 |url-status=live }}</ref> With a brace against [[1. FC Heidenheim|FC Heidenheim]], he became the first player to score 17 goals after 11 games of a Bundesliga season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67391194 |title=Bayern Munich 4–2 Heidenheim: Harry Kane breaks 11-game Bundesliga record with double |website=BBC Sport |date=11 November 2023 |access-date=11 November 2023 |archive-date=26 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231126131632/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67391194 |url-status=live }}</ref> With his 18th league goal in a victory over [[1. FC Köln|FC Köln]] on 24 November, he became the top scoring Englishman in a single season in Bundesliga history, surpassing [[Kevin Keegan]] and [[Jadon Sancho]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/67525853 |title=Kane scores again as Bayern back on top of the Bundesliga with 1–0 win over Cologne |website=BBC Sport |date=24 November 2023 |accessdate=13 January 2024 |archive-date=13 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240113095829/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/67525853 |url-status=live }}</ref>

With his 22nd league goal in a victory over [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] on 12 January 2024, he matched [[Robert Lewandowski]]'s record for most goals in the first half of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gokhale |first=Aditya |date=12 January 2024 |title=Harry Kane equals ANOTHER record as he matches Robert Lewandowski's haul of 22 goals in first half of Bundesliga season |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/harry-kane-matches-robert-lewandowski-record-22-goals-first-half-bundesliga-season/blt45c1eb67d68ccf1b |access-date=12 January 2024 |website=Goal |archive-date=12 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240112230625/https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/harry-kane-matches-robert-lewandowski-record-22-goals-first-half-bundesliga-season/blt45c1eb67d68ccf1b |url-status=live }}</ref> On 3 February, he netted a goal in 3–1 victory against [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]], matching [[Luca Toni]]'s record of 24 goals for Bayern on his debut season in 2007–08,<ref>{{cite web |last=Mills |first=Richard |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/harry-kane-goal-bayern-munich-record-luca-toni-2007-debut-season-bundesliga/blt94c4206926557f2c |title=Sensational Harry Kane equals Bayern Munich goal record that's been in place for almost two decades as he brings up No.24 of unbelievable debut season in Gladbach win |website=Goal |date=3 February 2024 |access-date=3 February 2024 |archive-date=3 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240203192823/https://www.goal.com/en/lists/harry-kane-goal-bayern-munich-record-luca-toni-2007-debut-season-bundesliga/blt94c4206926557f2c |url-status=live }}</ref> and on 18 February, he surpassed that with a goal in a 3–2 loss to Bochum.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Emons |first=Michael |date=18 February 2024 |title=Bochum 3–2 Bayern Munch: Harry Kane goal not enough as Bayern lose third game in a row |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68332112 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=18 February 2024 |archive-date=18 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240218190344/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68332112 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 9 March, Kane achieved his fourth hat-trick of the regular season and first of the year in an 8–1 rout of [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]]. This performance made him the first debut player to score at least twice in eight different games.<ref>{{Cite news |date=9 March 2024 |title=Record-breaking Kane nets hat-trick as Bayern humble Mainz 8–1 |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/record-breaking-kane-nets-hat-trick-bayern-humble-mainz-8-1-2024-03-09/ |access-date=9 March 2024 |work=Reuters}}</ref> On 16 March, Kane set a new personal best in league goalscoring during a match against Darmstadt 98, contributing one goal in a 5–2 victory, bringing his league total for the season to 31. This match also saw Kane breaking [[Uwe Seeler]]'s record of 30 goals scored in a Bundesliga debut season.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Thomas |first=Marissa |date=16 March 2024 |title=Darmstadt 98 2–5 Bayern Munch: Harry Kane sets personal best for league goals in a season |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68586255 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=16 March 2024 |archive-date=7 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607104428/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68586255 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 3 May 2024, Kane was announced as part of the [[Bundesliga Awards|Bundesliga Team of the Season]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/vote-now-for-the-bundesliga-team-of-the-season-2023-24-with-ea-fc-24-26961 |title=Confirmed: Bundesliga Team of the Season 2023/24 by EA FC 24! |publisher=Bundesliga |date=4 May 2024 |access-date=3 May 2024 |archive-date=21 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240521120757/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/vote-now-for-the-bundesliga-team-of-the-season-2023-24-with-ea-fc-24-26961 |url-status=live }}</ref> marking his seventh official seasonal team award and first time spanning multiple leagues. His 36 goals in his debut Bundesliga season, earned him the [[European Golden Shoe]], becoming the second English player to achieve this feat after [[Kevin Phillips (English footballer)|Kevin Phillips]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/european-golden-shoe-2024-standings-rankings/c963b1d057202059a5b8789f |title=European Golden Shoe 2023/24 standings: Updated rankings as Harry Kane leads race to be named Europe's best goalscorer |publisher=Sporting News |date=26 May 2024 |access-date=27 May 2024 |archive-date=27 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240527085533/https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/european-golden-shoe-2024-standings-rankings/c963b1d057202059a5b8789f |url-status=live }}</ref> In addition, he concluded the season as the [[List of UEFA Champions League top scorers#Top scorers by season|Champions League top scorer]] with eight goals, along with [[Kylian Mbappé]].<ref name="auto2">{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0285-1906eba1bea4-31faa14228af-1000--champions-league-top-scorers-2023-24-harry-kane-and-kylian-m/ |title=Champions League top scorers 2023/24: Harry Kane and Kylian Mbappé top the charts |publisher=UEFA |date=1 June 2024 |access-date=1 June 2024 |archive-date=23 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240523090108/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0285-1906eba1bea4-31faa14228af-1000--champions-league-top-scorers-2023-24-harry-kane-and-kylian-m/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He was also named in the Team of the Season in that competition.<ref name="auto3"/>

==== 2024–2025: First major title and Bundesliga Player of the Season====
[[File:FC Red Bull Salzburg gegen Bayern München (2025-01-06 Testspiel) 28.jpg|thumb|upright|Kane with [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in 2025]]

On 16 August 2024, Kane scored his first goal of the season in the first match of Bayern Munich's competitive campaign in a 4–0 [[DFB-Pokal]] victory over [[SSV Ulm 1846]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-15 |title=Bayern Munich ease through in DFB Cup on Vincent Kompany's competitive debut |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/ulm-bayern-munich-live-dfb-cup-preview-blog-report-kane-kompany-28485 |access-date=2024-09-15 |website=[[Bundesliga]]}}</ref> On 1 September, Kane scored his first regular season goal of the season when he converted penalty kick in a 2–0 victory over [[SC Freiburg]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-01 |title=Harry Kane and Thomas Müller on target as Bayern Munich beat Freiburg |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayern-munich-freiburg-free-highlights-preview-report-kane-musiala-kompany-28646 |access-date=2024-09-15 |website=[[Bundesliga]]}}</ref> On 14 September, Kane scored his first hat-trick of the campaign with the help of a penalty in a 6–1 victory over newly promoted [[Holstein Kiel]], which also meant that he has scored at least one goal against every Bundesliga side he has faced.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-14 |title=Harry Kane scores against Holstein Kiel to reach another Bayern Munich milestone |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/harry-kane-bayern-munich-goal-record-holstein-kiel-28934 |access-date=2024-09-15 |website=[[Bundesliga]]}}</ref> Three days later, Kane recorded a second consecutive hat-trick when he netted four times past [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] with the help of three penalties in a 9–2 victory in the first match of Bayern Munich's [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] campaign.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-17 |title=On-fire Bayern rout Dinamo |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/matches/profis/champions-league/2024-2025/fc-bayern-muenchen-dinamo-zagreb-17-09-2024/report |access-date=2024-09-17 |website=[[FC Bayern Munich]]}}</ref> With 33 goals, he became the highest-scoring Englishman in the Champions League, beating the previous record of 30 by [[Wayne Rooney]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/harry-kane-champions-league-record-wayne-rooney-b2614723.html |title='I keep all the balls': Harry Kane breaks Wayne Rooney's Champions League record with rare hat-trick |work=Independent |date=18 September 2024 }}</ref> On 21 September, Kane scored in a 5–0 win over [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]], overtaking [[Jadon Sancho]] to become the highest-scoring Englishman in the Bundesliga.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cx2kd5gxj7et|title=Werder Bremen 0–5 Bayern Munich|publisher=BBC Sport|date=21 September 2024|access-date=21 September 2024}}</ref> On 22 November, Kane scored a hat-trick against FC Augsburg to become the fastest player to reach 50 goals in the Bundesliga. He scored 50 goals in 43 Bundesliga games, overtaking [[Erling Haaland]]'s record of 50 in 50.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c1dp920e5lrt|title=Bayern Munich 3-0 Augsburg: Harry Kane quickest player to 50 Bundesliga goals after hat-trick|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> His next Bundesliga record was scoring 55 goals in 50 games after he netted twice against Holstein Kiel in a 4–3 win.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kimmich: "Wenn wir unsere Prinzipien verlieren, sind wir eine normale Mannschaft" |url=https://www.kicker.ch/kimmich-wenn-wir-unsere-prinzipien-verlieren-sind-wir-eine-normale-mannschaft-1087241/artikel |access-date=2025-02-02 |website=kicker |language=de-CH}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://talksport.com/football/2870533/harry-kane-bayern-munich-bundesliga-record/ |title= Harry Kane smashes Bundesliga record on landmark Bayern Munich appearance |first=Alex |last=Conrad|date=1 February 2025|work=talkSport}}</ref>

On 4 May 2025, Kane won his first major honour, the [[2024–25 Bundesliga]] title, where following a draw against RB Leipzig the previous day (Kane was unable to partake in that match due to a suspension because of an accumulation of yellow cards), Bayer Leverkusen could only manage a draw against SC Freiburg, mathematically crowning Bayern champions with two games to spare.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/may/04/harry-kane-bayern-munich-finally-trophy-long-craved-bundesliga | title = Harry Kane, Munich's beloved import, finally has the trophy he's long craved | website = The Guardian | date = 4 May 2025 | access-date = 4 May 2025 | first = Andy | last = Brassell}}</ref> On 11 May, Kane lifted the first trophy of his career as Bayern Munich celebrated their Bundesliga title success. Kane finished the season as the top scorer for the second consecutive season and was named the Bundesliga Player of the Season recognising his continued outstanding performances with Bayern Munich.<ref name=":1">{{cite web |date=20 May 2025 |title=Harry Kane wins Bundesliga top scorer award for second season in a row |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/harry-kane-2024-25-top-scorer-second-time-bayern-munich-most-goals-award-32191 |access-date=21 May 2025 |website=Bundesliga |publisher=Deutsche Fußball Liga}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{cite web |date=21 May 2025 |title=Harry Kane named Bundesliga Player of the Season for 2024/25 |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/harry-kane-bundesliga-player-of-the-season-2024-25-32339 |access-date=21 May 2025 |website=Bundesliga |publisher=Deutsche Fußball Liga}}</ref>

==== 2025–2026: Domestic double and goalscoring records====
On 16 August 2025, Kane achieved his second career title, scoring a goal in a 2–1 victory over [[VfB Stuttgart]] in the [[2025 Franz Beckenbauer Supercup|Franz Beckenbauer Supercup]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Kelly |first=Calum Preston |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/feels-good-harry-kane-celebrates-second-career-trophy-bayern-munich-stuttgart-german-super-cup/blt05c62224ed08f5c8#cs2050fe01ec877ed6 |title='Oh, it feels good!' - Harry Kane celebrates with second career trophy after Bayern Munich beat Stuttgart in German Super Cup |publisher=Goal.com |date=17 August 2025 }}</ref> Six days later in the opening game of the [[2025–26 FC Bayern Munich season|2025–26 Bundesliga season]], he scored a second-half hat-trick against RB Leipzig.<ref>{{cite news |last=Millington |first=Adam |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cdx042d0p0pt |title=Bayern Munich 6–0 RB Leipzig: Harry Kane scores hat-trick in rout |publisher=BBC Sport |date=22 August 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://talksport.com/football/3496489/harry-kane-bayern-munich-hat-trick-bundesliga/ |title=Harry Kane in stunning career first as Bayern Munich hero matches Premier League tally in 256 games fewer |first=Joe |last=Brophy |publisher=talkSPORT |date=22 August 2025 }}</ref> In the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League league phase|league phase]] of the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League]], Kane scored twice against Chelsea to help win the game 3–1, and overtake David Beckham to became the Englishman with the most goals and assists combined in the Champions League,<ref>{{cite web |url= https://talksport.com/football/3565202/harry-kane-david-beckham-record-champions-league-chelsea/ |title= Kane overtakes Beckham to make Champions League history as he dismantles Chelsea|work=talkSport |date=17 August 2025|first=Robert |last=Calcutt }}</ref> and only the third player (after Cristiano Ronaldo and [[Neymar]]) to have scored 20 or more goals for two different clubs in the Champions League.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://worldsoccertalk.com/news/harry-kane-rewrites-uefa-champions-league-history-with-new-record-cristiano-ronaldo-and-neymar-welcome-bayern-star-to-elite-list/ |title=Harry Kane rewrites UEFA Champions League history with new record: Cristiano Ronaldo and Neymar welcome Bayern star to elite list |first=Martina |last=Alcheva|date=19 September 2025 |work=World Soccer Talk }}</ref> On 26 September, Kane scored twice in a 4–0 victory over [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]], and became the fastest player to reach 100 goals for any club in one of Europe's top 5 leagues in the 21st century, having done so in 104 games, beating the previous record reached in 105 games by Cristiano Ronaldo and [[Erling Haaland]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cn955rz8wy8t |title=Bayern Munich 4 : 0 Werder Bremen |first=Alex |last=Brotherton |date=26 September 2025}}</ref> A month later, on 18 October, he scored his 400th career club goal in a 2–1 victory over Borussia Dortmund.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/articles/harry-kane-joins-the-elite-400-goals-and-comparisons-with-lionel-messi-and-cristiano-ronaldo-2025-10-19 |title=Harry Kane Joins the Elite: 400 Goals and Comparisons With Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=19 October 2025 }}</ref> On 29 October, Kane scored twice against [[1. FC Köln|Köln]] in the [[2025–26 DFB-Pokal|German Cup]] and helped the club win 4–1; this was the 14th straight victory for the club, the best start for any club in Europe's top five leagues.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://talksport.com/football/3690203/harry-kane-bayern-munich-record-most-wins-start-season/ |title=Harry Kane inspires Bayern Munich to football record that may never be broken |first=Joe |last=Brophy|date=30 October 2025 |work=talkSport}}</ref> Later that year, on 6 December, he scored his 10th Bundesliga hat-trick in a 5–0 away victory against Stuttgart, setting the record after just 76 matches.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/vfb-stuttgart-bayern-munich-match-report-highlights-matchday-13-35089 |title=Harry Kane hits hat-trick off bench as five-star Bayern brush Stuttgart aside |publisher=Bundesliga |date=6 December 2025 }}</ref> On 14 December, he scored from the penalty spot in a 2–2 draw against Mainz 05, reaching 474 career goals and surpassing the previous record held by [[Jimmy Greaves]] to become the highest-scoring English player in history.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://iffhs.com/posts/4814 |title=HARRY KANE BROKE THE RECORD ! |publisher=IFFHS |date=20 December 2025 }}</ref> A week later, on 21 December, he reached his 100th Bundesliga goal contribution, comprising 81 goals and 19 assists, by scoring a stoppage-time goal in a 4–0 away victory over Heidenheim, achieving the milestone in 78 matches and surpassing the previous record of [[Roy Makaay]] (113 appearances).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/harry-kane-record-100-goal-involvements-bayern-munich-heidenheim-35306 |title=Harry Kane smashes yet another Bundesliga record in Bayern Munich's victory over Heidenheim |publisher=Bundesliga |date=21 December 2025 }}</ref>

On 14 February 2026, Kane scored a brace in a 3–0 away win over Werder Bremen, reaching his 500th career goal in 743 appearances, with 100 of those coming from penalties.<ref>{{cite web |last=Cunningham |first=Jack |url=https://talksport.com/football/3985126/harry-kane-new-milestone-faster-cristiano-ronaldo-stats-500-goals/ |title=Harry Kane reaches stunning new milestone faster than Cristiano Ronaldo |publisher=talkSPORT |date=14 February 2026 }}</ref> He scored twice in a 4–1 win against [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] on 18 March, reaching the landmark of 50 Champions League goals in 66 games.<ref>{{cite news |last=Rose |first=Gary |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cj4zjj7g40et |title=Bayern Munich 4–1 Atalanta |work=BBC Sport |date=18 March 2026 }}</ref> On 7 April, he scored in a 2–1 away win over Real Madrid at the [[Bernabéu (stadium)|Bernabéu]], securing his club's first victory at the ground since May 2001 and their first win over the opposition since April 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/02a4-2055ba2b6033-0e7e190d47fb-1000--real-madrid-1-2-bayern-munchen-diaz-and-kane-pounce-for-sh/ |title=Real Madrid 1-2 Bayern München highlights: Luis Díaz and Harry Kane pounce in Champions League quarter-final first leg |publisher=UEFA |date=7 April 2026 }}</ref> Kane also scored an equaliser in the return leg the following week to take him to 50 goals for the season, the first time he had ever done so.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7180922/2026/04/15/harry-kane-bayern-munich-50-goals/|title=The numbers behind Harry Kane's sensational 50-goal season|first=Will|last=Jeanes|date=15 April 2026|work=The Athletic|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> He also reached his 12th goal in the competition, surpassing his previous record, in a 4–3 victory, as his side qualified to the semi-finals with a 6–4 aggregate win.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ames |first=Nick |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/apr/15/bayern-munich-real-madrid-champions-league-quarter-final-second-leg-match-report |title=Díaz and Olise late show sends Bayern into semi-finals after Real Madrid classic |work=The Guardian |date=15 April 2026 }}</ref> On 19 April, he scored in a 4–2 win over Stuttgart as his club secured their 35th Bundesliga title and it would also be his second major trophy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c89558d5d5nt |title=Bayern Munich 4–2 Stuttgart |publisher=BBC Sport |date=19 April 2026 }}</ref> On 28 April, he scored in his sixth consecutive Champions League match during a 5–4 defeat to [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]], becoming the first English player to reach this milestone and surpassing [[Steven Gerrard]]'s previous record.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/48620592/bayern-harry-kane-breaks-steven-gerrard-record-psg-thriller |title=Bayern Munich's Harry Kane breaks Steven Gerrard's record in PSG thriller |publisher=ESPN |date=28 April 2026 }}</ref> In addition, he moved into Bayern's [[List of FC Bayern Munich records and statistics#Goalscorers|all-time top ten scorers]], equaling [[Giovane Élber]]'s tally of 139 goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/de/news/harry-kane-breaks-into-bayern-munichs-all-time-top-10-goalscorers-42792094 |title=Harry Kane breaks into Bayern Munich's all-time top 10 goalscorers |publisher=OneFootball |date=30 April 2026 }}</ref> A week later, on 6 May, he scored a stoppage-time equalizer in a 1–1 draw against Paris Saint-Germain, but his team was eliminated after losing the tie 6–5 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite web |last=McNulty |first=Phil |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/ce3py2d7dwvt |title=Bayern Munich 1–1 Paris Saint-Germain |publisher=BBC Sport |date=6 May 2026 }}</ref> Hence, he scored in six consecutive knockout-stage matches, equaling a record set by [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] between 2012 and 2013.<ref>{{cite web |last=Pathak |first=Shivam |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/48696811/harry-kane-bayern-munich-equals-cristiano-ronaldo-mark-misses-champions-league-golden-boot |title=Harry Kane equals Cristiano Ronaldo mark, misses Champions League golden boot |publisher=ESPN |date=7 May 2026 }}</ref> However, he reached his 55th goal of the season for the club, matching Robert Lewandowski's record in 2019–20.<ref>{{cite web |last=Riley |first=Martha |url=https://talksport.com/football/4237425/arsenal-psg-champions-league-final-harry-kane-record/ |title=Arsenal to face Paris Saint-Germain in Champions League final as Harry Kane equals stunning record |publisher=talkSPORT |date=6 May 2026 }}</ref> On 16 May, he scored a hat-trick in a 5–1 win over FC Köln, equaling his Bundesliga record of 36 goals, securing the top scorer award for a third consecutive season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayern-munich-cologne-kane-hattrick-match-report-highlights-matchday-34-37426 |title=Harry Kane hat-trick as Bayern Munich thrash Cologne in season finale |publisher=Bundesliga |date=16 May 2026 }}</ref><ref name=":2">{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/harry-kane-top-scorer-2025-26-third-time-bayern-munich-37407 |title=Bayern Munich's Harry Kane wins Bundesliga top scorer award for third straight season |publisher=Bundesliga |date=16 May 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Calcutt |first=Robert |url=https://talksport.com/football/4263273/harry-kane-bayern-munich-robert-lewandowski-goals-record/ |title=Harry Kane smashes Robert Lewandowski record and breaks surprise Michael Ballack tally |publisher=talkSPORT |date=16 May 2026 }}</ref> On 23 May, Kane scored a hat-trick in Bayern's 3–0 victory over VfB Stuttgart in the [[2026 DFB-Pokal final|DFB-Pokal final]], setting a new club record for the 21st century with 61 goals in all competitions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c5ye92n53zgt |title=Bayern Munich 3-0 Stuttgart: Harry Kane hat-trick wins German Cup |publisher=BBC Sport |first=Sam |last=Drury |date=23 May 2026}}</ref> He ultimately secured his second European Golden Shoe trophy, and surpassed [[Dixie Dean]]'s 1927–28 English record of 60 goals in a season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/harry-kane-caps-incredible-season-with-european-golden-shoe-42919847 |title=Harry Kane caps incredible season with European Golden Shoe |publisher=OneFootball |date=25 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
===2010–2015: Youth level===
[[File:Harry Kane.jpg|thumb|upright|Kane warming up for [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]] at the [[2012 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]]]]

In January 2010, Kane was called up to play for the [[England national under-17 football team|England under-17 team]] for the Algarve Tournament in Portugal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefootballnetwork.net/main/s565/st153364.htm |title=U17 squad announced |date=23 January 2010 |publisher=Thefootballnetwork.net |access-date=15 January 2011 |archive-date=16 May 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100516163743/http://www.thefootballnetwork.net/main/s565/st153364.htm |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane missed the [[2010 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]] due to illness, with England going on to win the tournament in his absence.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/mar/25/harry-kane-england-inspiration |last=Hytner |first=David |title=Harry Kane is an inspiration to all the young England players coming through |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=25 March 2015 |access-date=30 March 2015 |archive-date=12 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412065247/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/mar/25/harry-kane-england-inspiration |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored two goals in six appearances in total at under-17 level.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.englandfootballonline.com/MatchRsl/MatchRslTmU17.html |title=Match Results Under 17: 1982–2010 |website=England Football Online |date=31 August 2024 |access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref> He later moved up to the [[England national under-19 football team|under-19s]] and scored twice in a 6–1 victory over [[Albania national under-19 football team|Albania]] on 8 October 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.england-mad.co.uk/roll/edb2/england_u19_6_albania_u19_1_567840/index.shtml |title=England U19 6 Albania U19 1 |date=8 October 2010 |publisher=england-mad.co.uk |access-date=15 January 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120317053936/http://www.england-mad.co.uk/roll/edb2/england_u19_6_albania_u19_1_567840/index.shtml |archive-date=17 March 2012 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Kane played a large role in the England under-19s progression to the semi-finals of the [[2012 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]] in Estonia. Kane scored the winner against [[France national under-19 football team|France]] in the final group stage match to ensure the team a safe passage through to the semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tottenham striker Kane delighted to be in England scoring form in U19 Euros |date=11 July 2012 |url=http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/tottenham-striker-kane-delighted-be-engand-scoring-form-u19-euros-3343721 |publisher=Tribal Football |access-date=21 March 2015 |archive-date=2 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402133401/http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/tottenham-striker-kane-delighted-be-engand-scoring-form-u19-euros-3343721 |url-status=live}}</ref> In total, Kane appeared 14 times for the England under-19 team and contributed six goals during that period.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.englandfootballonline.com/MatchRsl/MatchRslTmU19pg2.html |title=Match Results Under 19: 2010–2019 |website=England Football Online |date=12 September 2024 |access-date=12 September 2024}}</ref>

On 28 May 2013, he was named in manager [[Peter Taylor (footballer, born 1953)|Peter Taylor]]'s 21-man [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup squads#England|squad]] for the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=England U20s Head Coach Peter Taylor names his 21-man squad for World Cup |url=http://www.thefa.com/england/mens-u20s/News/2013/u20s-world-cup-squad-announcement-280513 |website=[[The Football Association]] |access-date=21 March 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130607185327/http://www.thefa.com/england/mens-u20s/News/2013/u20s-world-cup-squad-announcement-280513 |archive-date=7 June 2013 |date=28 May 2013}}</ref> He made his debut on 23 June in the opening group-stage match, a 2–2 draw against [[Iraq national under-20 football team|Iraq]], in which he assisted [[Luke Williams (footballer, born 1993)|Luke Williams]]' goal.<ref>[http://www.thefa.com/england/mens-u20s/News/2013/iraq-updates-230613 "England v Iraq"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131209053925/http://www.thefa.com/england/mens-u20s/News/2013/iraq-updates-230613 |date=9 December 2013 }} The Football Association. 23 June 2013. Retrieved 24 June 2013/</ref> Kane then scored in the following match against [[Chile national under-20 football team|Chile]], collecting a pass after work by [[Ross Barkley]] and shooting from the edge of the [[penalty area]].<ref>[http://www.thefa.com/england/mens-u20s/News/2013/engchi_matchreport "All square in Antalya"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927221701/http://www.thefa.com/england/mens-u20s/News/2013/engchi_matchreport |date=27 September 2013 }} The Football Association. 26 June 2013. Retrieved 26 June 2013.</ref> On 13 August, Kane made his debut for the [[England national under-21 football team|under-21s]] against [[Scotland national under-21 football team|Scotland]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Harry Kane |url=http://www.thefa.com/england/all-teams/players/k/harry-kane |publisher=The Football Association |access-date=21 March 2015 |archive-date=16 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160316151115/http://www.thefa.com/england/all-teams/players/k/harry-kane |url-status=dead}}</ref> In that match, he came on as a substitute in the 58th minute, and England won 6–0.<ref>{{cite web |title=England Under-21s beat Scotland U21s 6–0 |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/live/match/292365/report |website=Sky Sports |access-date=21 March 2015 |archive-date=2 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402135131/http://www1.skysports.com/football/live/match/292365/report |url-status=live}}</ref> On 10 October, he scored a hat-trick for England against [[San Marino national under-21 football team|San Marino]] in [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification]].<ref name="Soccerway">{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/harry-kane/158575/ |title=H. Kane: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=11 March 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231028202704/https://uk.soccerway.com/players/harry-kane/158575/ |archive-date=28 October 2023 |url-status=dead}}</ref>

Kane was named in the England under-21 [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship squads#England|squad]] for the [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]] in the Czech Republic, despite opposition from his club manager Mauricio Pochettino.<ref>{{cite news |title=England Under-21s: Harry Kane in European Championship squad |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32807828 |access-date=20 May 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=20 May 2015 |archive-date=22 May 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150522034139/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32807828 |url-status=live}}</ref> He played every minute of England's campaign at the tournament, which ended with them eliminated in last place in their group.<ref>{{cite news |title=Portugal begin with win against England |url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2015368--england-vs-portugal/ |access-date=23 August 2015 |publisher=UEFA |date=18 June 2015 |archive-date=11 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811134450/https://www.uefa.com/under21/season=2015/matches/round=2000408/match=2015368/index.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=England beat Sweden through late Lingard goal |url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2015374--sweden-vs-england/ |access-date=23 August 2015 |publisher=UEFA |date=21 June 2015 |archive-date=16 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180116182800/http://www.uefa.com/under21/season=2015/matches/round=2000408/match=2015374/index.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Italy beat England but Sweden deny them semi spot |url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2015378--england-vs-italy/ |access-date=23 August 2015 |publisher=UEFA |date=24 June 2015 |archive-date=15 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615015134/http://www.uefa.com/under21/season=2015/matches/round=2000408/match=2015378/index.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

===2015–2018: Senior debut and first major tournaments===
[[File:Laurent Koscielny of France marking England striker Harry Kane (22695724617).jpg|thumb|Kane (in white) playing for [[England national football team|England]] against [[France national football team|France]] in 2015]]

Kane was also eligible for the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]] through his father, who was born in Galway,<ref name="galway"/> but in August 2014 he ruled out switching allegiance, saying that he wanted to break into the [[England national football team|England senior team]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Blow for Martin O'Neill as Harry Kane rules out playing for the Republic of Ireland |url=https://www.independent.ie/sport/soccer/blow-for-martin-oneill-as-harry-kane-rules-out-playing-for-the-republic-of-ireland-30547200.html |newspaper=Irish Independent |location=Dublin |date=29 August 2014 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=15 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615163314/https://www.independent.ie/sport/soccer/blow-for-martin-oneill-as-harry-kane-rules-out-playing-for-the-republic-of-ireland-30547200.html |url-status=live}}</ref>
 
After a good run of form with Tottenham and being the third top goalscorer in the Premier League with 16 goals, on 19 March 2015, Kane was named by manager [[Roy Hodgson]] in the England squad to face [[Lithuania national football team|Lithuania]] in a [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying]] match and [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in a friendly.<ref name=ENG>{{cite news |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/england/2015/mar/england-squad-named-lithuania-italy |title=Harry Kane earns first call-up to England senior squad |publisher=The Football Association |date=19 March 2015 |access-date=19 March 2015 |first=Jamie |last=Bradbury |archive-date=4 May 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150504020746/http://www.thefa.com/news/england/2015/mar/england-squad-named-lithuania-italy |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his international debut at [[Wembley Stadium]], replacing [[Wayne Rooney]] in the second half against Lithuania, and scored just 80 seconds later with a header from a [[Raheem Sterling]] cross.<ref>{{cite news |last=McNulty |first=Phil |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31968091 |title=England 4–0 Lithuania |website=BBC Sport |date=27 March 2015 |access-date=29 May 2016 |archive-date=3 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603180856/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31968091 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 30 March 2015, the day before the Italy match, Hodgson announced that Kane would start alongside Rooney,<ref>{{cite news |title=Tottenham's Harry Kane to start for England against Italy |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32028730 |access-date=30 March 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=20 March 2015 |archive-date=1 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150401022452/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32028730 |url-status=live}}</ref> and he played the full 90 minutes of the 1–1 draw at [[Juventus Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy 1–1 England |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32028730 |access-date=31 March 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=31 March 2015 |archive-date=1 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150401022452/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32028730 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In his next appearance on 5 September 2015, substitute Kane scored the fifth of England's six goals in a win over [[San Marino national football team|San Marino]] which qualified them for [[UEFA Euro 2016]].<ref>{{cite news |last=McNulty |first=Phil |title=San Marino 0–6 England |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33273427 |website=BBC Sport |date=5 September 2015 |access-date=29 May 2016 |archive-date=4 June 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160604063844/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33273427 |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane scored his third England goal against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] in another qualifier three days later, which they won 2–0.<ref>{{cite news |last=McNulty |first=Phil |title=England 2–0 Switzerland |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34061844 |website=BBC Sport |date=8 September 2015 |access-date=29 May 2016 |archive-date=1 April 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160401022453/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34061844 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 12 October, as England finished their qualification campaign with a tenth win from ten matches, Kane's shot hit the post for an own goal by Lithuanian goalkeeper [[Giedrius Arlauskis]] in a 3–0 away victory.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lithuania 0–3 England |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33544077 |access-date=12 October 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=12 October 2015 |archive-date=12 October 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151012214453/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33544077 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 22 May 2016, Kane opened the scoring in a 2–1 friendly win over [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] at the [[City of Manchester Stadium]], but later missed a penalty. He was the first England player to fail to score from the penalty spot during a game since [[Frank Lampard]] in 2010, and the first to miss the target since [[Peter Crouch]] in 2006.<ref>{{cite news |last=Chris |first=Bevan |title=England 2–1 Turkey |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36295279 |website=BBC Sport |date=22 May 2016 |access-date=29 May 2016 |archive-date=24 June 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200624111120/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36295279 |url-status=live}}</ref> At the European Championship in France that June, Kane was assigned to take [[corner kick]]s, a tactic which was criticised by pundits,<ref>{{cite news |last=Smith |first=Peter |title=Why is Harry Kane on corners? England striker's new role criticised |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/12016/10311456/why-is-harry-kane-on-corners-england-strikers-new-role-criticised |access-date=28 June 2016 |website=Sky Sports |date=13 June 2016 |archive-date=24 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180624175350/http://www.skysports.com/football/news/12016/10311456/why-is-harry-kane-on-corners-england-strikers-new-role-criticised |url-status=live}}</ref> but defended by Hodgson, who said that Kane was the best for the role.<ref>{{cite news |last=Cross |first=John |title=England boss Roy Hodgson defends using striker Harry Kane to take corner kicks 9 |url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-match-reports/england-boss-roy-hodgson-defends-8175351#p2eQCjKSBvXAfECV.97 |access-date=28 June 2016 |newspaper=Daily Record |location=Glasgow |date=13 June 2016 |archive-date=22 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230522214455/https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-match-reports/england-boss-roy-hodgson-defends-8175351#p2eQCjKSBvXAfECV.97 |url-status=live}}</ref> He failed to score at the tournament as England were eliminated by [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] at the [[UEFA Euro 2016 knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12016/10327555/englands-harry-kane-struggled-to-replicate-his-tottenham-form-at-euro-2016-but-why|title=England's Harry Kane struggled to replicate his Tottenham form at Euro 2016 - but why?|access-date=30 June 2024|website=Sky Sports}}</ref>

On 10 June 2017, Kane [[List of England national football team captains|captained England]] for the first time in their [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group F|2018 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] with [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] at [[Hampden Park]], scoring an added-time equaliser to rescue a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Scotland 2–2 England |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40141512 |website=BBC Sport |date=10 June 2017 |access-date=11 June 2017 |archive-date=24 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181024193030/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40141512 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 5 October, he scored an added-time winner against [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]] which confirmed England's qualification to the 2018 FIFA World Cup.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/oct/05/england-slovenia-world-cup-qualifier-match-report |title=Harry Kane late strike against Slovenia secures England's World Cup place |last=Taylor |first=Daniel |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=5 October 2017 |access-date=6 October 2017 |archive-date=24 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190424181153/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/oct/05/england-slovenia-world-cup-qualifier-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref>

===2018–2020: Captaincy and FIFA World Cup Golden Boot===
[[File:Harry Kane 2018.jpg|thumb|upright|Kane playing for [[England national football team|England]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]

Kane was named in the 23-man [[2018 FIFA World Cup squads#England|England squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] and was named captain.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44138600 |title=England World Cup squad: Trent Alexander-Arnold in 23-man squad |website=BBC Sport |date=16 May 2018 |access-date=17 May 2018 |archive-date=16 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180516133910/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44138600 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/12016/11381470/harry-kane-to-captain-england-at-world-cup-in-russia |title=Harry Kane to captain England at World Cup in Russia |website=Sky sports |date=22 May 2018 |access-date=22 May 2018 |archive-date=9 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709202846/http://www.skysports.com/football/news/12016/11381470/harry-kane-to-captain-england-at-world-cup-in-russia |url-status=live}}</ref> On 18 June, Kane scored both of England's goals in a 2–1 win over [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]], his winning goal coming deep in injury time, in the team's opening group game of the World Cup.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jun/18/tunisia-england-world-cup-match-report |title=Kane double ensures England defeat Tunisia in World Cup opener |first=Daniel |last=Taylor |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=19 June 2018 |access-date=19 June 2018 |archive-date=18 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618223854/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jun/18/tunisia-england-world-cup-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref> In the next group game on 24 June, Kane scored a [[List of England national football team hat-tricks|hat-trick in England]]'s 6–1 win over [[Panama national football team|Panama]], which was England's largest ever World Cup victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331546/#match-liveblog |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143258/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331546/#match-liveblog |url-status=dead |archive-date=12 June 2018 |title=England 6–1 Panama: Live blog |publisher=FIFA |access-date=16 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44595397 |title=World Cup: England set new records in 6–1 victory over Panama |website=BBC Sport |date=24 June 2018 |access-date=16 July 2018 |archive-date=18 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718112122/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44595397 |url-status=live}}</ref> With his three goals against Panama, Kane became the third England player to score a [[List of FIFA World Cup hat-tricks|hat-trick in a World Cup]] match, after [[Geoff Hurst]] against [[Germany national football team|West Germany]] in the [[1966 FIFA World Cup final|1966 final]] and [[Gary Lineker]] against [[Poland national football team|Poland]] in 1986.<ref>{{cite news |title=England thrash Panama to reach last 16 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44439183 |website=BBC Sport |issue=24 June 2018 |date=24 June 2018 |access-date=24 June 2018 |archive-date=25 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625123435/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44439183 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Kane scored his sixth goal of the finals from a penalty kick in England's [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]] tie with [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]]. He also scored the team's first kick of the [[penalty shoot-out]] as England prevailed 4–3; this was the first time that England had managed to win a [[List of FIFA World Cup penalty shoot-outs|penalty shoot-out at the World Cup]].<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44610244 "World Cup 2018: England beat Colombia 4–3 on penalties] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220525200213/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44610244 |date=25 May 2022}}. BBC. Retrieved 4 July 2018</ref> Kane didn't score again for the rest of the tournament as England finished in fourth place after losing 2–0 [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] in the third-place playoff.<ref>{{cite news |title=World Cup 2018: England finish fourth after Belgium defeat |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44748604 |access-date=14 July 2018 |website=BBC Sport |archive-date=19 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190519105251/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44748604 |url-status=live}}</ref> However, his six goals in the tournament earned him the [[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Boot|Golden Boot]] as the top goalscorer of the World Cup, the first England player to win the award since Gary Lineker became the first to do so in [[1986 FIFA World Cup|the 1986 tournament]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.sky.com/story/harry-kane-set-for-golden-boot-after-world-cup-final-in-moscow-11437608 |title=England captain Harry Kane wins Golden Boot as World Cup ends |website=Sky News |access-date=15 July 2018 |archive-date=31 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210131055829/https://news.sky.com/story/harry-kane-set-for-golden-boot-after-world-cup-final-in-moscow-11437608 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/2018/07/15/world-cup-2018-golden-boot-standings-will-harry-kane-finish/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/2018/07/15/world-cup-2018-golden-boot-standings-will-harry-kane-finish/ |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=World Cup 2018 golden boot final standings: Harry Kane wins after finishing as top scorer |date=15 July 2018 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=15 July 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref>

The September international break saw the introduction of the [[UEFA Nations League]]. England's first match was on 8 September 2018 against [[Spain national football team|Spain]], which Kane captained for the full 90 minutes in a game which saw England lose 2–1.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/england-vs-spain/teams/399710 |title=UEFA Nations League |website=Sky Sports |access-date=19 November 2018 |archive-date=30 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130234609/https://www.skysports.com/football/england-vs-spain/teams/399710 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 15 October, England played Spain for the second time in the [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League A#Group 4|group]], this time running out 3–2 winners with Kane assisting two of the three goals.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/spain-vs-england/teams/399775 |title=UEFA Nations League |website=Sky Sports|access-date=19 November 2018|archive-date=6 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206033128/https://www.skysports.com/football/spain-vs-england/teams/399775|url-status=live}}</ref> On 14 November, before a friendly against the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]], Kane presented [[Wayne Rooney]] with England's Golden Boot in recognition of Rooney's [[List of international goals scored by Wayne Rooney|53 England goals]], a record that, at the time, made him England's all-time top goalscorer. In an interview following the match, which ended in a 3–0 win for England, Rooney revealed that he wanted Kane to present him the award, correctly predicting that Kane overtake him as all-time top goalscorer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/rooney-kane-will-beat-my-england-scoring-record/1cvmuurocub861htftolc2jwf5 |title=Wayne Rooney: Harry Kane will beat my England scoring record |website=Goal |access-date=19 November 2018 |archive-date=30 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130224312/https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/rooney-kane-will-beat-my-england-scoring-record/1cvmuurocub861htftolc2jwf5 |url-status=live}}</ref> Three days after the United States match, Kane captained England in their final Nations League group match against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] as the Three Lions won 2–1. Kane first assisted [[Jesse Lingard]]'s equaliser then scored the winning goal which saw England top the group and qualify for the [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals|Nations League Finals]] in June 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/england-vs-croatia/teams/399808 |title=UEFA Nations League |website=Sky Sports |access-date=19 November 2018 |archive-date=22 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022152639/https://www.skysports.com/football/england-vs-croatia/teams/399808 |url-status=live}}</ref>

===2021–present: Euro finals and all-time England top scorer===
In the [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying|qualifying phase]] of [[UEFA Euro 2020]], Kane captained the 1,000th match played by England, and scored a hat-trick against [[Montenegro national football team|Montenegro]]. This brought his tally to 31, which placed him sixth in the all-time list of England's top goalscorers and also made him the highest-ever scoring England captain.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/harry-kane-becomes-england-highest-ever-goalscoring-captain-a4287696.html |title=Harry Kane becomes England's highest-ever goalscoring captain |first=Tom |last=Doyle |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |date=14 November 2019 |access-date=14 November 2019 |archive-date=5 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210205045224/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/harry-kane-becomes-england-highest-ever-goalscoring-captain-a4287696.html |url-status=live}}</ref> The 7–0 win also secured England's qualification to [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/international/england-vs-montenegro-result-score-5-things-we-learned-kane-oxlade-chamberlain-rashford-a9203656.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220509/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/international/england-vs-montenegro-result-score-5-things-we-learned-kane-oxlade-chamberlain-rashford-a9203656.html |archive-date=9 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=England vs Montenegro: 5 things we learned as Harry Kane hat-trick helps Three Lions clinch Euro 2020 spot |first=Jack |last=Rathborn |newspaper=The Independent |date=14 November 2019}}</ref> Kane was in fine form throughout the qualifying process, becoming the first Englishman to score in every game in a qualifying campaign, registering a total of twelve goals – the joint-most for an England player in a single year.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12016/11863384/kosovo-0-4-england-gareth-southgates-side-end-emphatic-qualification-campaign-on-a-high |title=Kosovo 0–4 England: Gareth Southgate's side end emphatic qualification campaign on a high |website=Sky Sports |access-date=17 November 2019 |archive-date=2 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210202131142/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12016/11863384/kosovo-0-4-england-gareth-southgates-side-end-emphatic-qualification-campaign-on-a-high |url-status=live}}</ref>

In the [[UEFA Euro 2020 knockout stage#Round of 16|Euro 2020 round of 16]] match on 29 June 2021, Kane scored the second goal against [[Germany national football team|Germany]]. This was his first goal of the tournament in a 2–0 victory for England.<ref>{{Cite news |title=England end 55-year wait for knockout win over Germany |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51198606|access-date=29 June 2021|archive-date=1 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210701085405/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51198606|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored a further two goals in the quarter-finals match against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] on 3 July.<ref>{{Cite news |title=England thrash Ukraine to make last four |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51198691|access-date=3 July 2021|archive-date=11 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210711103245/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51198691|url-status=live}}</ref> In the semi-final against [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]], Kane scored the winning goal in a 2–1 triumph that secured England's place in the [[UEFA Euro 2020 final|Euro 2020 final]], the country's first final in a major competition since [[1966 FIFA World Cup|1966]], which they subsequently lost to [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in a penalty shootout after a 1–1 draw in regular time.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51198755 |title=England reach Euro 2020 final |author=Phil McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=7 July 2021 |access-date=7 July 2021 |archive-date=8 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210708173854/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51198755 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Italy20">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51198762 |title=Euro 2020 final: England beaten by Italy on penalties |author=Phil McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=11 July 2021 |access-date=14 November 2021 |archive-date=13 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210713012900/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51198762 |url-status=live}}</ref> In the unsuccessful shootout, Kane did convert his penalty but England ultimately lost 3–2.<ref name="Italy20"/>

[[File:Harry Kane 2022 World Cup (cropped).jpg|thumb|Kane playing for [[England national football team|England]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]]]

In the last two [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Albania national football team|Albania]] and [[San Marino national football team|San Marino]], Kane scored back-to-back first-half hat-tricks (including a "[[Hat-trick#Perfect hat-trick|perfect hat-trick]]" against the former and four goals against the latter) to help secure England's qualification to the [[2022 FIFA World Cup|tournament]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane helps himself to four as England hit San Marino for 10 |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/sport/soccer/international/harry-kane-helps-himself-to-four-as-england-hit-san-marino-for-10-1.4729614 |access-date=20 December 2021 |newspaper=The Irish Times |archive-date=18 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118143155/https://www.irishtimes.com/sport/soccer/international/harry-kane-helps-himself-to-four-as-england-hit-san-marino-for-10-1.4729614 |url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2022, in the league phase of the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League]], Kane scored his 50th international goal in the game against Germany, making him only the second player to score 50 goals for England, only three goals behind [[Wayne Rooney]] in the all-time England top-scorer list.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/blog-the-toe-poke/story/4682105/harry-kane-nets-50th-england-goal-what-are-some-of-his-best |title=Harry Kane nets 50th England goal: What are some of his best? |first=Chris |last=Wright |date=8 June 2022 |publisher=ESPN |access-date=8 June 2022 |archive-date=8 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220608115946/https://www.espn.com/soccer/blog-the-toe-poke/story/4682105/harry-kane-nets-50th-england-goal-what-are-some-of-his-best |url-status=live}}</ref> At the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], Kane scored twice, enough to equal Rooney's all-time top-scoring record, as England reached the quarter-finals; however they were eliminated by France after he missed a penalty in their 2–1 defeat.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Anguish for Kane on night he levels England record |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/61666027 |date=11 December 2022 |access-date=14 December 2022 |archive-date=10 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221210203451/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/61666027 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 23 March 2023, he scored a penalty in a [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifier]] to help England win 2–1 over reigning European champions Italy, which was also England's first away win against Italy since 1961.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64972899 |title=Italy 1 : 2 England |first=Phil |last=McNulty |date=23 March 2023 |website=BBC Sport|access-date=24 March 2023|archive-date=25 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230325175339/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64972899|url-status=live}}</ref> This goal, his 54th for England, overtook Rooney's record and made Kane England's all-time record goalscorer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64945178 |title=Harry Kane breaks Wayne Rooney's all-time England goalscoring record |website=BBC Sport |date=24 March 2023|access-date=24 March 2023 |archive-date=24 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230324002024/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64945178|url-status=live}}</ref> Kane achieved this feat with 39 fewer games than Rooney, with a score rate of 0.7 goals per game, higher than most of England's recent top goalscorers.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/mar/24/harry-kane-reels-in-rooney-for-england-goals-record-like-a-hunter-with-its-prey |title=Harry Kane reels in Rooney for England goals record like a hunter with its prey |first=David |last=Hytner |date=24 March 2023 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=24 March 2023|archive-date=24 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230324121413/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/mar/24/harry-kane-reels-in-rooney-for-england-goals-record-like-a-hunter-with-its-prey|url-status=live}}</ref> On 17 October, he scored a brace in a 3–1 win against Italy in the second leg of the Euro 2024 qualifier, which was England's first win against their opponent at Wembley Stadium since 1977.<ref>{{cite web |author=Phil McNulty |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67061856 |title=England 3–1 Italy |website=BBC Sport |date=17 October 2023|access-date=19 October 2023|archive-date=18 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231018030042/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67061856|url-status=live}}</ref>

In June 2024, Kane was named in England's 26-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cv22menk7dno |title=Eze & Wharton named in England squad for Euro 2024 |website=BBC Sport |date=6 June 2024 |access-date=6 June 2024 |archive-date=6 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240606170808/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cv22menk7dno |url-status=live }}</ref> He captained England to a 1–0 win over [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] in their opening [[UEFA Euro 2024 Group C|Group C]] match on 16 June,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cz992dxd4xwt#Line-ups|title=Hungary 1–3 Switzerland LIVE: UEFA Euro 2024 - score, updates & reaction|website=BBC Sport|access-date=17 June 2024}}</ref> overtaking [[Gary Neville]] as England's outright most capped player at [[England at the UEFA European Championship|European Championships]] with his 12th Euros appearance. It was also his 23rd appearance at a major tournament, giving him the outright record ahead of [[Ashley Cole]] and [[Raheem Sterling]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-ie/sports/other/harry-kane-sets-three-all-time-england-records-during-serbia-clash/ar-BB1ol8D9|title=Harry Kane sets three all-time England records during Serbia clash|access-date=21 June 2024|website=MSN}}</ref> On 20 June, in the second group match against Denmark, he scored his first goal of the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2024/jun/20/denmark-england-euro-2024-live-updates|title=Denmark v England: Euro 2024 – live updates|date=20 June 2024|access-date=21 June 2024|website=The Guardian}}</ref> Kane scored the winning goal of England's [[UEFA Euro 2024 knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]] win over [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]] with a header in the first minute of extra time. This match was his 79th appearance for England in a competitive match, breaking the record of [[Peter Shilton]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028e-1b41ff0c9b9e-382c1ab22a1d-1000--england-2-1-slovakia-aet-bellingham-and-kane-earn-comeba/|title=England 2–1 Slovakia (AET): Bellingham and Kane earn comeback win|date=28 June 2024|access-date=1 July 2024|website=UEFA}}</ref> Kane scored the equaliser against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]], with a penalty in the first half of the semi-final. He started for England in the [[UEFA Euro 2024 final|final]] against Spain, but was substituted in the 61st minute,<ref name="EU24"/> as England lost the final 2–1.<ref name="EU24"/> With three goals in the tournament, Kane was awarded the [[UEFA European Championship awards#Golden Boot|Golden Boot]] in a six-way tie. He became the third player ever to win the award at both the Euros and World Cup, after [[Valentin Ivanov (footballer, born 1934)|Valentin Ivanov]] and [[Dražan Jerković]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/football/story/_/id/40558317/euro-2024-golden-boot-harry-kane-dani-olmo-6-winners |title=Euro 2024 Golden Boot: Harry Kane, Dani Olmo among 6 winners |website=ESPN|date=14 July 2024|access-date=15 July 2024}}</ref>

Having won his 100th cap for the senior national team with a tally of 66 goals scored in 99 games, Kane made his centennial appearance for England on 10 September 2024 in a 2–0 home win against [[Finland national football team|Finland]] in the Nations League, scoring both goals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c36n934x5l6o|title='Night belongs to him and his golden boots' - Kane's 100 caps in numbers|publisher=BBC Sport|date=9 September 2024|access-date=21 September 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/match/2040088--england-vs-finland/|title=England 2–0 Finland|website=[[UEFA]]|date=9 September 2024|access-date=21 September 2024}}</ref> On 14 October 2025, he scored a brace in a 5–0 away win over [[Latvia national football team|Latvia]], securing his nation's qualification to the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Calcutt |first=Robert |url=https://talksport.com/football/3646867/england-qualify-world-cup-harry-kane-history-latvia/ |title=England seal place at 2026 World Cup as Harry Kane makes history in Latvia thrashing |publisher=talkSPORT |date=14 October 2025 }}</ref>

==Player profile==
===Development===
Kane's former youth coach [[Alex Inglethorpe]] has said of him:<blockquote>When he first came into the under-18s as a 15 year old, he stood out in the sense he looked a bit gangly. He moved slightly awkwardly, he was a bit cumbersome. But look closer, he had a lot of ability, a great technique. I think he surprised people how good he was. Tactically he was very flexible. He often played in midfield. I remember seeing him once playing as a [[Midfielder#Holding midfielder|holding midfielder]].<ref name=jim/></blockquote>

As a teenager, Kane initially struggled in Tottenham's academy, partially due to his date of birth in July and the so-called ''Relative Age Effect'',<ref>{{cite web |url= https://summerbornchildren.org/2020/03/18/sports-initiative-helps-young-players-overcome-birth-month-disadvantage/ |title=Sports Initiative Helps Young Players Overcome Birth Month Disadvantage |website=summerbornchildren.org |date=18 March 2020 |access-date=24 September 2024}}</ref> he was not as physically developed as other players, nor was he as quick. However, he gained the respect of coaches with his technique and desire for self-improvement.<ref name=jim>{{cite news |last=White |first=Jim |title=Harry Kane's incredible journey from Arsenal reject to Tottenham hero |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/tottenham-hotspur/11335368/Harry-Kanes-incredible-journey-from-Arsenal-reject-to-Tottenham-hero.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/tottenham-hotspur/11335368/Harry-Kanes-incredible-journey-from-Arsenal-reject-to-Tottenham-hero.html |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |date=9 January 2015 |access-date=6 December 2017}}{{cbignore}}</ref>

When profiling Kane in February 2013, [[Talksport]] said that he was best as a [[second striker]], despite also having ability as a [[centre forward]] or in a [[Winger (association football)|wide position]].<ref name=talksport>{{cite news |last=Roden |first=Lee |title=Is this Tottenham starlet the man to solve the club's striker crisis? |url=http://talksport.com/magazine/features/130204/tottenham-starlet-man-solve-clubs-striker-crisis-190960 |access-date=8 February 2015 |publisher=Talksport |date=4 February 2013 |archive-date=12 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171012053418/http://talksport.com/magazine/features/130204/tottenham-starlet-man-solve-clubs-striker-crisis-190960 |url-status=live}}</ref> They wrote that he preferred to place his shots, although he could also score from distance.<ref name=talksport/> The report also noted that he had good pace, but was weak in the air and had not scored on his loan at Norwich.<ref name=talksport/> Initially a back-up to £26&nbsp;million Spanish import Roberto Soldado and frequently loaned out, Kane was eventually made Tottenham's starting forward by manager Mauricio Pochettino.<ref name=jim/> Under Pochettino, Kane said that his game has improved through the tough training techniques instituted by the manager.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/av/football/31852098 |title=Pochettino key to my improvement – Kane |date=13 March 2015 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=12 February 2018 |archive-date=30 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231030225433/https://www.bbc.com/sport/av/football/31852098 |url-status=live}}</ref> He also strives to achieve marginal gain to maximise his potential by tweaking various aspects of his training and preparations as well as nutrition.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/oct/04/harry-kane-england-marginal-gains |title=Harry Kane turns to kitchen rather than training ground for England recipe |first=Dominic |last=Fifield |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=4 October 2017 |access-date=2 February 2018 |archive-date=2 February 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180202152512/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/oct/04/harry-kane-england-marginal-gains |url-status=live}}</ref>

===Analysis===
Former Tottenham manager [[David Pleat]] described Kane as an "old-fashioned traditional centre-forward".<ref name=mcnulty/> [[Clive Allen]], who coached him at Tottenham, stated that "one thing I'd say about him, which unfortunately you don't say about a lot of young footballers, is that he had a passion for the game. He loves football, he loves playing, he loves scoring goals".<ref name=mcnulty/> His former Tottenham under-21 coach [[Les Ferdinand]] likened Kane's movement to their former forward Teddy Sheringham, and the power and accuracy of his shots to Alan Shearer.<ref name=jim/>

A tall and physical striker,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/espn/feature/story/_/id/26247752/harry-kane-wants-conquer-premier-league-nfl |title=Harry Kane wants to conquer the Premier League ... then the NFL |publisher=ESPN |last1=Schoenfeld |first1=Bruce |date=27 March 2019 |access-date=6 October 2019 |archive-date=7 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007021514/http://www.espn.com/espn/feature/story/_/id/26247752/harry-kane-wants-conquer-premier-league-nfl |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldsoccer.com/features/player-profile-harry-kane-407201 |title=Player Profile: Harry Kane |website=World Soccer |publisher=TI Media |last1=Tremlett |first1=Sam |date=18 September 2018 |access-date=6 October 2019 |archive-date=10 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410164211/https://www.worldsoccer.com/features/player-profile-harry-kane-407201 |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane's style of play has been compared to that of former Tottenham forward [[Jürgen Klinsmann]], a comparison Kane called flattering in February 2015.<ref>{{cite news |last=Palmer |first=Kevin |title=Harry Kane flattered by Jurgen Klinsmann comparisons |url=http://www.espnfc.com/tottenham-hotspur/story/2281527/harry-kane-flattered-by-jurgen-klinsmann-comparisons |access-date=8 February 2015 |website=ESPN FC |date=5 February 2015 |archive-date=20 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220165609/http://www.espnfc.com/tottenham-hotspur/story/2281527/harry-kane-flattered-by-jurgen-klinsmann-comparisons |url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2015, [[Football Association]] chairman [[Greg Dyke]] named Kane as the benchmark for clubs producing young English players.<ref name=stuff/> Shearer said that month that the three best strikers playing in the league were Kane, Diego Costa and Sergio Agüero.<ref>{{cite news |title=Shearer on the Barclays Premier League's top four strikers |url=http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/news/news/2014-15/mar/090315-alan-shearer-on-diego-costa-sergio-aguero-harry-kane-charlie-austin.html |access-date=9 March 2015 |publisher=Premier League |date=9 March 2015 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150311145830/http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/news/news/2014-15/mar/090315-alan-shearer-on-diego-costa-sergio-aguero-harry-kane-charlie-austin.html |archive-date=11 March 2015}}</ref> Although he was initially criticised for his limited aerial game in his early career, as well as his lack of significant pace,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/harry-kane-isn-t-especially-fast-powerful-or-good-in-the-air.-in-other-words-he-could-be-the-new_sto4718736/story.shtml |title=Harry Kane isn't especially fast, powerful or good in the air. In other words, he could be the new |publisher=Eurosport |date=7 May 2015 |access-date=29 October 2021}}</ref> he became more prolific with his head as his career progressed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/12166715/back-antonee-robinson-to-grab-his-first-fulham-assist-at-14-1-jones-knows |title=Back Harry Kane to score with a header at 10/1 – Jones Knows |publisher=Sky Sports |last1=Jones |first1=Lewis |date=19 December 2020 |access-date=29 October 2021 |archive-date=29 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211029004853/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/12166715/back-antonee-robinson-to-grab-his-first-fulham-assist-at-14-1-jones-knows |url-status=live}}</ref>

After Tottenham's victory over Chelsea in January 2015, blogger Chris Miller wrote, "Nobody thought he was the guy who was going to give that performance against Chelsea".<ref name=jim/> In February 2015, [[BBC Sport]] wrote that Kane was best as a lone striker, with his "hold-up play and close control" making him apt in other positions as well.<ref name=mcnulty>{{cite news |last=McNulty |first=Phil |title=Harry Kane: England's next number nine? |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31395579 |access-date=11 February 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=10 February 2015 |archive-date=12 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150212061820/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31395579 |url-status=live}}</ref> Also that month, ''[[Match of the Day]]'' pundit [[Danny Murphy (footballer, born 1977)|Danny Murphy]] said that the England team should be built around Kane, stating, "I'm struggling to see a weakness in the lad's game".<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane: Build England around striker – Murphy |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31204958 |access-date=8 February 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=8 February 2015 |archive-date=9 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150209222137/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31204958 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In August 2018, [[ESPN FC|ESPN]] reporter Michael Cox said that "Kane was initially considered a pure goal scorer, he's actually a good all-round player, often playing as an attacking midfielder", stating that during the 2018 FIFA World Cup "Kane's contributions in deeper positions were outstanding, his back-to-goal work as impressive as ever".<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane's versatility for Tottenham makes him more than a pure goal scorer |date=17 August 2018 |access-date=17 August 2018 |first=Michael |last=Cox |publisher=ESPN |url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/club/tottenham-hotspur/367/blog/post/3600185/harry-kanes-versatility-for-tottenham-makes-him-more-than-a-pure-goal-scorer |archive-date=17 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180817161250/http://www.espn.co.uk/football/club/tottenham-hotspur/367/blog/post/3600185/harry-kanes-versatility-for-tottenham-makes-him-more-than-a-pure-goal-scorer |url-status=live}}</ref> Indeed, although Kane is predominantly known for his clinical finishing and prolific goalscoring ability as an out-and-out striker, he is also known for his vision, technique, link-up play, and passing ability, which enables him to drop deep, bring his teammates into play, and create chances for other players; he is therefore also capable of playing in a more creative role as a [[false 9]] or even as a [[Attacking midfielder|number 10]].<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.si.com/thecauldron/2015/10/22/tottenham-harry-kane-english-premier-league-goals |title=Unlucky Tottenham striker Harry Kane is poised for a goal-scoring binge |magazine=Sports Illustrated |last1=Thomsen |first1=Blake |date=22 October 2015 |access-date=6 October 2019 |archive-date=6 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006144120/https://www.si.com/thecauldron/2015/10/22/tottenham-harry-kane-english-premier-league-goals |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.squawka.com/en/features/explained-harry-kanes-role-england-spurs |title=Harry Kane's role change for England & Spurs explained |publisher=squawka.com |last1=Edwards |first1=Harry |date=24 March 2019 |access-date=6 October 2019 |archive-date=6 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006144117/https://www.squawka.com/en/features/explained-harry-kanes-role-england-spurs |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/tottenham-hotspur/11428129/Tottenham-striker-Harry-Kanes-all-round-ability-is-as-key-as-his-finishing-in-England-cause.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/tottenham-hotspur/11428129/Tottenham-striker-Harry-Kanes-all-round-ability-is-as-key-as-his-finishing-in-England-cause.html |archive-date=11 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Tottenham striker Harry Kane's all-round ability is as key as his finishing in England cause |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |last1=Hayward |first1=Paul |date=22 February 2015 |access-date=6 October 2019}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.squawka.com/en/premier-league-player-role-changes/ |title=Roles reinvented: Seven players who have undergone a tactical readjustment this season |publisher=Squawka |date=14 December 2020 |access-date=29 October 2021 |archive-date=29 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211029003730/https://www.squawka.com/en/premier-league-player-role-changes/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2022, Sam McGuire of [[Opta Sports]] identified him as "the most creative number 9 in the world."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Someoddpilot |first=Devs |date=10 December 2022 |title=How Harry Kane Turned Into the Most Creative Number 9 in the World |url=https://theanalyst.com/2022/12/how-harry-kane-turned-into-the-most-creative-number-9-in-the-world/ |access-date=19 February 2023 |website=The Analyst |archive-date=19 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230219130707/https://theanalyst.com/2022/12/how-harry-kane-turned-into-the-most-creative-number-9-in-the-world/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Additionally, he is also known for his defensive work-rate,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/55390827 |title=Why Kane is the ultimate team player – Shearer analysis |website=BBC Sport |last1=Shearer |first1=Alan |authorlink=Alan Shearer |date=22 December 2020 |access-date=29 October 2021 |archive-date=29 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211029004853/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/55390827 |url-status=live}}</ref> and is an accurate penalty taker.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/15122/11506011/harry-kane-the-premier-leagues-top-penalty-taker |title=Harry Kane: The Premier League's top penalty taker |website=Sky Sports |last1=Smith |first1=Peter |date=23 September 2018 |access-date=1 July 2020 |archive-date=1 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200701135329/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/15122/11506011/harry-kane-the-premier-leagues-top-penalty-taker |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/49623572 |title=Harry Kane: England striker takes up to '50 penalties' a practice session |website=BBC Sport |date=7 September 2019 |access-date=1 July 2020 |archive-date=12 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191112103021/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/49623572 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Beginning in 2020, Kane started to be criticised about a perceived tactic of backing into defenders jumping for headers, causing the players to fall backwards onto the pitch, potentially risking serious injury.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Farry |first1=Wayne |title=Fans call for officials to take action on Harry Kane's 'dangerous' signature move |url=https://www.joe.co.uk/sport/fans-harry-kane-dangerous-signature-move-258079 |website=JOE.co.uk |date=7 December 2020 |publisher=Maximum Media |access-date=18 December 2020 |archive-date=14 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201214231519/https://www.joe.co.uk/sport/fans-harry-kane-dangerous-signature-move-258079 |url-status=live}}</ref> After doing so to [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] player [[Adam Lallana]] and winning a penalty, Kane was criticised by ex-Arsenal player [[Martin Keown]] who said, "He looks at his opponent, knows what he is going to do and makes a back for him. I think it is dangerous play from Harry Kane and he knows what he is doing and I don't even think it is a penalty."<ref>{{cite news |last1=Young |first1=Alex |title=Harry Kane guilty of 'dangerous play' to win Tottenham a penalty against Brighton, says Martin Keown |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/tottenham-news-harry-kane-brighton-martin-keown-dangerous-b39490.html |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |access-date=18 December 2020 |archive-date=2 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201102081056/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/tottenham-news-harry-kane-brighton-martin-keown-dangerous-b39490.html |url-status=live}}</ref> However, this tactic has been defended by Crystal Palace defender [[Gary Cahill]] who said, "I think that's just part of football. I think an element of that is being clever and experienced and knowing when you can maybe draw a foul in."<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ouzia |first1=Malik |title=Gary Cahill backs Harry Kane over controversial aerial challenges: 'They're just part of football' |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/gary-cahill-harry-kane-tottenham-crystal-palace-b272542.html |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |access-date=18 December 2020 |archive-date=12 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201212120326/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/gary-cahill-harry-kane-tottenham-crystal-palace-b272542.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

==Media and sponsorship==
Kane began a boot sponsorship deal with footwear company [[Skechers]] in August 2023<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.footballboots.co.uk/kaneboots.html |title=Harry's Skechers Deal |publisher=FootballBoots |date=17 August 2023 |access-date=18 August 2023 |archive-date=17 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230817224351/https://www.footballboots.co.uk/kaneboots.html |url-status=live}}</ref> after his agreement with sportswear and equipment supplier [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]] ended.<ref name="Nike"/> Following his [[List of Premier League players with 100 or more goals|100th Premier League goal]] in February 2018 Nike launched the special-edition Hypervenom 3 HK.<ref name="Nike">{{cite news |title=Nke Celebrates Harry Kane's 100th Premier League Goal with Special-Edition Hypervenom 3 HK |url=https://news.nike.com/news/harry-kane-100-premier-league-goal-hypervenom |agency=Nike.com |access-date=27 June 2018 |archive-date=27 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627144702/https://news.nike.com/news/harry-kane-100-premier-league-goal-hypervenom |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2018 he featured in a Nike commercial, "Nothing Beats a Londoner", along with other sports stars based in the city, including quadruple [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] champion [[Mo Farah]] and Chelsea playmaker [[Eden Hazard]], highlighting London's diversity.<ref>{{cite news |title=Nike advert, 'Nothing Beats A Londoner': Michael Dapaah, Harry Kane and Skepta in new ad highlighting London's diversity |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/video/News/nike-advert-watch-new-skepta-michael-dapaah-big-shaq-rio-ferdinand-video-harry-kane-nothing-beats-a-a8202981.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220509/https://www.independent.co.uk/video/News/nike-advert-watch-new-skepta-michael-dapaah-big-shaq-rio-ferdinand-video-harry-kane-nothing-beats-a-a8202981.html |archive-date=9 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |newspaper=The Independent |access-date=27 June 2018}}</ref> Ahead of [[UEFA Euro 2016]], Kane featured in advertisements for [[Mars Bars]] and [[Beats by Dr. Dre]] headphones, the latter alongside [[Antoine Griezmann]], [[Mario Götze]] and [[Cesc Fàbregas]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Bristow |first=Thomas |title=Harry Kane stars in awesome new advert alongside Antoine Griezmann and Mario Gotze |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/row-zed/harry-kane-stars-awesome-new-8139010 |access-date=27 June 2016 |newspaper=Daily Mirror |location=London |date=6 June 2016 |archive-date=12 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160712120658/http://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/row-zed/harry-kane-stars-awesome-new-8139010 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Kane features in [[EA Sports]]' [[FIFA (video game series)|''FIFA'' video game series]]: he was named to the Team of the Year in ''[[FIFA 18]]'', joining Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo in attack.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/01/24/fifa-18-team-week-19-announced-featuring-neymar-eden-hazard-7255991/ |title=FIFA 18 Team of the Week 19 announced featuring Neymar and Eden Hazard |first=Daniel |last=Mackrell |newspaper=Metro |location=London |date=24 January 2018 |access-date=19 June 2018 |archive-date=19 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619204020/https://metro.co.uk/2018/01/24/fifa-18-team-week-19-announced-featuring-neymar-eden-hazard-7255991/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Kane and [[Camila Cabello]] announced the winner of the "Best International Male Solo Artist" award at the [[2018 Brit Awards]] at [[The O2 Arena|the O<sub>2</sub> Arena]] on 21 February, namely [[Kendrick Lamar]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/blog/the-toe-poke/65/post/3393144/harry-kane-presents-brit-with-camila-cabello-trolled-by-arsenal-fan-host |title=Harry Kane presents Brit with Camila Cabello, trolled by Arsenal fan host |publisher=ESPN |date=21 February 2018 |access-date=22 February 2018 |archive-date=22 February 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180222225950/http://www.espn.com/soccer/blog/the-toe-poke/65/post/3393144/harry-kane-presents-brit-with-camila-cabello-trolled-by-arsenal-fan-host |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 14 May 2020, Kane announced that he would sponsor Leyton Orient's shirts for the next season to help support the first club he played for professionally through the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/52665809 |title=Harry Kane: England captain donates Leyton Orient shirt sponsorship to good causes |date=14 May 2020 |website=BBC Sport|access-date=17 May 2020|archive-date=15 May 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200515034605/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/52665809|url-status=live}}</ref> The unusual sponsorship deal, the first of its kind in English football, has the approval of Premier League, [[English Football League]] and Football Association, and the sponsorship has been donated to charities which will receive 10% of the proceeds of the respective shirt sales – the home shirt shows a thank you message to the NHS frontline workers tackling the pandemic, the away shirt sporting a logo of Haven House Children's Hospice while the third kit features the mental health charity [[Mind (charity)|Mind]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.leytonorient.com/2020/05/15/watch-harry-kane-on-good-morning-britain/ |title=WATCH: Harry Kane on Good Morning Britain |publisher=Leyton Orient F.C. |date=15 May 2020 |access-date=17 May 2020 |archive-date=9 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809141838/https://www.leytonorient.com/2020/05/15/watch-harry-kane-on-good-morning-britain/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.itv.com/news/2020-05-15/spurs-and-england-captain-harry-kane-pays-for-leyton-orient-sponsorship/ |title=Spurs and England captain Harry Kane pays for Leyton Orient sponsorship |date=15 May 2020 |website=ITV News|access-date=17 May 2020|archive-date=16 May 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200516170500/https://www.itv.com/news/2020-05-15/spurs-and-england-captain-harry-kane-pays-for-leyton-orient-sponsorship/|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Personal life==
In an interview given in February 2015, Kane said he was in a relationship with Katie Goodland, whom he has known since childhood.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/euro2016/tottenham-and-england-star-harry-kane-my-family-is-a-team-game-and-i-d-like-to-be-a-father-myself-a3273496.html |title=Tottenham and England star Harry Kane: My family is a team game — and I'd like to be a father myself one day |last=Churchill |first=David |newspaper=Evening Standard |location=London |date=16 June 2016|access-date=5 October 2017|archive-date=14 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200614003711/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/euro2016/tottenham-and-england-star-harry-kane-my-family-is-a-team-game-and-i-d-like-to-be-a-father-myself-a3273496.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He told ''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]],'' "We went to school together, so she's seen my whole career. Of course, she's finding it a little crazy. I think she's even been in the papers a couple of times, taking the dogs out."<ref name=esq/> On 1 July 2017, Kane announced his engagement to Goodland on his [[Twitter]] account,<ref>{{cite news |title=Harry Kane engaged to Kate Goodland |url=http://www.beinsports.com/us/premier-league/news/harry-kane-engaged-to-kate-goodland/583538 |access-date=6 October 2017 |publisher=beIN Sports |date=1 July 2017 |archive-date=6 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171006213847/http://www.beinsports.com/us/premier-league/news/harry-kane-engaged-to-kate-goodland/583538 |url-status=live}}</ref> and said in June 2019 that they had married.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.sky.com/story/harry-kane-marries-his-childhood-sweetheart-and-best-friend-11746719 |title=Harry Kane Marries His Childhood Sweetheart and 'Best Friend' |website=Sky News |date=22 June 2019 |access-date=15 August 2019 |archive-date=7 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107234809/https://news.sky.com/story/harry-kane-marries-his-childhood-sweetheart-and-best-friend-11746719 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Kane and Katie Goodland announced the birth of their first child, a daughter, in January 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/fa-league-cups/tottenham-vs-aston-villa-harry-kane-newly-born-daughter-pochettino-fa-cup-a7516481.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220509/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/fa-league-cups/tottenham-vs-aston-villa-harry-kane-newly-born-daughter-pochettino-fa-cup-a7516481.html |archive-date=9 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Tottenham vs Aston Villa: Harry Kane left out of Spurs match-day squad to be with newly-born daughter |first=Jack |last=Pitt-Brooke |date=8 January 2017 |newspaper=The Independent |location=London}}</ref> The birth of their second daughter was announced in August 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tottenham and England striker Harry Kane celebrates arrival of his second child |url=http://www.itv.com/news/london/2018-08-08/tottenham-and-england-striker-harry-kane-celebrates-arrival-of-his-second-child/ |access-date=8 August 2018 |website=ITV News |date=8 August 2018 |archive-date=20 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220165636/https://www.itv.com/news/london/2018-08-08/tottenham-and-england-striker-harry-kane-celebrates-arrival-of-his-second-child/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Their first son was born in December 2020,<ref>{{cite tweet |user=HKane |number=1344665751173607425 |title=Our beautiful boy has arrived. 29/12/2020. Louis Harry Kane. |date=31 December 2020}}</ref> and their second son was born in August 2023.<ref>{{Cite news |date=21 August 2023 |title=Harry Kane erneut Vater geworden: Erstes Tor, viertes Kind |language=de |website=Der Spiegel |publisher=Spiegel-Gruppe |url=https://www.spiegel.de/panorama/leute/bayern-star-harry-kane-wird-zum-vierten-mal-vater-a-a295aaa1-bf40-4586-ad43-e0bede4bac11 |access-date=21 August 2023 |issn=2195-1349 |archive-date=21 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230821201726/https://www.spiegel.de/panorama/leute/bayern-star-harry-kane-wird-zum-vierten-mal-vater-a-a295aaa1-bf40-4586-ad43-e0bede4bac11 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Kane and Goodland have two [[Labrador retrievers]], Brady and Wilson. He named one after [[NFL]] quarterback [[Tom Brady]]. In response to a suggestion that the other dog's name was a reference to NFL quarterback [[Russell Wilson]], Kane stated: "My wife actually named the other one Wilson. People just assumed it was for Russell Wilson. But it was just a coincidence."<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sportsmole.co.uk/off-the-pitch/spurs/news/kane-passes-obedience-course-with-dogs_245037.html |title=Tottenham Hotspur star Harry Kane 'helps pet dogs pass obedience course' |last=Joynson |first=Danielle |date=9 September 2015|access-date=25 July 2016 |website=Sports Mole|archive-date=17 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817012113/http://www.sportsmole.co.uk/off-the-pitch/spurs/news/kane-passes-obedience-course-with-dogs_245037.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-12 |title=Brady the dog & Harry Kane in NFL! Bayern Munich striker has American dream after already taking inspiration from gridiron greats |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/brady-dog-harry-kane-nfl-bayern-munich-striker-american-dream-inspiration-gridiron-greats/bltd251d9a21c5d06ac |access-date=2025-05-21 |website=www.goal.com}}</ref> Kane has cited ''The Brady 6'', a documentary about Brady, as an inspiration for his development.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2018/05/31/football-nfl-world-cup-harry-kane-england-ndamukong-suh-andrew-luck |title=Football meets Fútbol: The mutual admiration of global stars |last=Wahl |first=Grant |magazine=Sports Illustrated|access-date=9 February 2019|archive-date=9 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190209232218/https://www.si.com/soccer/2018/05/31/football-nfl-world-cup-harry-kane-england-ndamukong-suh-andrew-luck|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2019, Kane expressed an interest in becoming a [[Placekicker|kicker]] in the NFL "in 10 to 12 years".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nfl.com/news/harry-kane-wants-to-be-nfl-kicker-in-10-or-12-years-0ap3000001024523 |title=Harry Kane wants to be NFL kicker 'in 10 or 12 years' |publisher=National Football League|access-date=7 June 2019|archive-date=7 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607200845/http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001024523/article/harry-kane-wants-to-be-nfl-kicker-in-10-or-12-years|url-status=live}}</ref>

Kane abstains from alcohol during the football season, and starting from 2017, he hired a full-time chef to optimise his nutrition.<ref>{{cite news |last=Pitt-Brooke |first=Jack |title=Harry Kane credits 2017 form to new nutrition regime as he is named temporary England captain |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/international/harry-kane-england-captain-spurs-tottenham-nutrition-chef-kitchen-2017-goals-a7983456.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220509/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/international/harry-kane-england-captain-spurs-tottenham-nutrition-chef-kitchen-2017-goals-a7983456.html |archive-date=9 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |newspaper=The Independent |location=London |date=4 October 2017 |access-date=2 February 2018}}</ref> He plays golf in his free time. As of 2024, he is a 3 [[handicap (golf)|handicap]].<ref name=esq>{{cite news |last=Parker |first=Sam |title=Harry Kane: "To Score At Wembley Is What You Dream About As A Kid" |url=https://www.esquire.com/uk/culture/news/a8396/harry-kane-models-the-seasons-sharpest-suits/ |access-date=27 August 2015 |magazine=Esquire |date=3 June 2015 |archive-date=9 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210609132110/https://www.esquire.com/uk/culture/news/a8396/harry-kane-models-the-seasons-sharpest-suits/ |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-01 |title=Soccer star Harry Kane on what separates great golfers from good ones |url=https://golf.com/news/harry-kane-separate-great-golfers-from-good/?amp=1 |access-date=2025-05-21 |website=Golf}}</ref>

Kane was appointed a [[Member of the Order of the British Empire]] (MBE) in the [[2019 New Year Honours]] for services to football.<ref name=MBE>{{London Gazette |issue=62507 |supp=y |page=N19 |date=29 December 2018}}</ref>

On 10 October 2022, Kane launched the Harry Kane Foundation, which "seeks to change perceptions of mental health by normalising conversations and promoting positive habits to end stigma around the subject". To mark the occasion, Kane featured on ''[[CBeebies]]' Bedtime Stories''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63180793 |title=Harry Kane: England and Tottenham striker to read bedtime story on CBeebies |website=BBC Sport|access-date=10 October 2022|archive-date=9 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221009231040/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63180793|url-status=live}}</ref>

A mural of Kane outside the Tottenham Hotspur Stadium was unveiled in May 2023 in celebration of Kane becoming Tottenham's record goalscorer. Kane and his family left their handprints and signatures on the bottom of the mural.<ref>{{cite web|title=Harry's record celebrated with mural in the heart of Tottenham Tottenham Hotspur|date=15 May 2023|website=tottenhamhotspur.com|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2023/may/harry-s-record-celebrated-with-mural-in-the-heart-of-tottenham/|access-date=18 March 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kane visits his mural... and adds his own finishing touches Tottenham Hotspur|date=19 May 2023|website=tottenhamhotspur.com|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2023/may/kane-visits-his-mural-and-adds-his-own-finishing-touches/|access-date=18 March 2025}}</ref> A [[Statue of Harry Kane|statue of Kane]] commissioned by [[Waltham Forest Council]] in 2020, though a permanent location was debated for years, leaving the statue in storage until November 2024, when the statue was unveiled at the [[Peter May (cricketer)|Peter May]] Sports Centre in [[Walthamstow]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Harry Kane poses as his controversial statue is unveiled after years locked away | website=STV News | date=18 November 2024 | url=https://news.stv.tv/world/harry-kane-poses-as-his-controversial-statue-is-unveiled-after-years-locked-away | access-date=18 November 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Harry Kane: England captain looks to play on for country beyond 2026 World Cup | website=BBC Sport | date=18 November 2024 | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c8xp7r4ve24o | access-date=19 November 2024}}</ref>

